And who does he see walking in, but Liz, the woman he has been in love with for ages. "This is an interesting situation," thought Clive. Spurred on, that Liz thinks she needs help as much as he does, Clive strides into the auditorium with renewed purpose.  He takes a seat near the front, and prepares to have his life changed.

It was a bittersweet feeling though, because despite the fact that the others didn't work out, there had been something about the guys that she just felt an intense connection to. They dated for a while, and she began to feel like she was falling in love. Until one night over a take out dinner and a movie he asked her about her past relationships. She could lie and act like they had all been horrible, but it had always been her policy to be honest and mature. She told him about the guys she had dated, and how she had felt an intense connection to them. She was worried that she might be going overboard by telling him about the good points of each.

They mention they are all reincarnations of the same person, including yourself. They have been watching the lives of each incarnation, and will continue to do so for who knows how long.  You are then are silenced, and are told the next reincarnation will begin their lives soon, and you along with your past reincarnations all begin watching your next life on the big screen. 

You see the new incarnation born in a different country, and with a different family. It starts off innocently enough, with the birth of the new reincarnation in a different hospital than you were born.

You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching yourself on the big screen. 9a29f841869a4fd98cf358da50f4a340.prefix:
When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen. While totaly confused, I still felt calm and after looking up and seeing my parents on the screen holding me as a child, I sat down and started to enjoy the show.  The movie was about my life, and I was the main character. It was a film of my life as if it was being shot by a high budget, production studio. I watched my life unfold in front of my eyes, and it was amazing. I was able to see everything that I had done, and there was even a narration of my inner thoughts. I lived a pretty good life, for the most part anyway. 
After the movie me and all the other me's which must have numbered in the thousands went into the lobby to interact with each other and to mainly try to find out what was going on. We were all confused, but we all seemed to be in a good mood at least. Yes, I should be frightened and confused but instead I feel as though this is where I am meant to be. We all then started to ask each other why they thought we were here and what was this place. We all had crazy ideas since we were all sci-fi geeks except for .0021% of us. Then the lights started to flash and it was time to head back in. 
We entered the theater but this time the screen was gone and a man who resembled my dad was onstage. 
"Welcome to the afterlife" he said.
9a29f841869a4fd98cf358da50f4a340.infix: Well not really, more like, Welcome to real life.

Ctrl-G.suggestion: We all looked at each other and then back at him.

b43dca37a1704c10990f320c35f2828f.prefix:
When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen. As your next life unfolds, you experience all kinds of emotions. You laugh and cry at so many scenes, you watch them go by with no accounting for time. You have no idea how much time is passing. You can't feel it and there is no timekeeping mechanism on display, anywhere in the theater. You are just watching your next life, and you are watching it unfold in real time.

It feels so odd to watch day turn to night, and months pass, on screen. You don't feel bored and you have no concept of time passing, in your space. You wonder how all of this is possible? How can you be watching your next life, in real time, and how can you be watching it in a theater, with other people who look just like you? These questions are huge. You decide to ask one of the other audience members, a woman sitting right next to you. She shrugs her shoulders and speaks, but you don't understand the language. You return the shrug, but don't bother speaking. 

You look back at the screen, and you see your next life unfold. You see every mistake that you make in your next life. You want so badly to tell your next self not to make so many mistakes, but you are powerless to do so.

You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen. You can see in detail the events that will occur in your next life, but you're unable to interact with the movie. You wish you could take this knowledge into your next life, but you know you can't. You don't even remember any of your other past lives besides the one you just lived.

You are shocked to learn that you have been both male and female in past lives, both rich and poor, and have died both young and old. The most surprising life you lived was as royalty in a middle eastern country. You were a princess who had her pick of men. You married a man you didn't love, but who was a decent person and an excellent king. It was enough for you to know that your husband would take good care of your people. Eventually, you grew to love him because of his kindness and generosity.

You watched your movie life and learned that you would soon be reincarnated as a man in Japan.

Today is the culmination of all of our hard work; the energy from the Mana would be focused into a vessel, granting them extraordinary power. The ceremony was taking place in the center of the city, in a large open area. Large, needlelike stones stood around the ring, focusing the Mana's flow.   The energy would be focused into a single person, who would become the savior of humanity. 

I watched in awe as more and more people showed up for the choosing ceremony. 
The Mana was flowing through the city, and the needle-like stones were glowing brightly. On an Altar in the middle of the room, 
the energy wisped into a curling ball of rolling light. It was beautiful. 

The light seemed to be taking a form, and I could see a shape in the center of the light. It was a man, with a long, flowing cloak. But it faded away, and was replaced by another. This one was a woman, with long, flowing hair.  Several other forms appeared and then vanished inside the swirling light.

All of the "#1 Dad" mugs in the world change to show the actual ranking of Dads suddenly.

It seemed like a normal day as Jeff staggered down the hall into the kitchen to make his morning coffee before taking a shower and getting ready for work. He grabbed for his "#1 Dad" mug that his kids got him for Father's Day last year. As he filled it with coffee he noticed that instead of saying "#1 Dad" it said "#5467 Dad" Jeff set the mug down and rubbed his eyes. He knew he wasn't quite awake yet. He looked at the mug again and sure enough, #5467. Huh, kids must be playing a joke. As he was about to head to the shower he noticed that his other mug that his wife bought him shortly after their daughter was born said "#5467 Dad". He was dumbfounded. "They really went all in on this prank" Jeff thought to himself as he jumped in the shower. 

He got dressed and headed off to work.

As he drove to work, he noticed a lot of people out and about in his neighborhood yelling at each other in various stages of dress. Some men in bathrobes other wearing nothing but boxer shorts and sandals all showing each other their coffee mugs. Jeff rolled down his windows to ask what was going on. Mr, Jennings, Jeff's neighbor strolled over to the window and leaned in and said "Finkel here says he is a better dad than me and he can prove it! So he whips out this coffee mug that says "#8243 Dad" on it. I laughed at him and went in to get my mug that my kids got me for Christmas that said "#1 Dad" on it but I could only find this one that said "#12845 Dad" on it" tears were welling up in his eyes.
79b6b33580664bc1b5c608eb32156bab.infix: "Oh well, I'm sure you'll find the other one soon.

Ctrl-G.suggestion: Jeff couldn't believe what he was hearing.

gpt-3.5-turbo.suggestion: Jeff couldn't shake off the oddity of the situation.

gpt-4-turbo.suggestion: Jeff's bewilderment grew as he processed Mr. Jennings' story.

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. She could lie and act like they had all been horrible, but it had always been her policy to be honest and mature. She was afraid to see his expression and was sure he did not have a pleasant one. But she was helpless to stop. It was as if she was compelled to keep telling him about the others and unable to tell him anything but the truth.

You are then are silenced, and are told the next reincarnation will begin their lives soon, and you along with your past reincarnations all begin watching your next life on the big screen. 

You see the new incarnation born in a different country, and with a different family. It starts off innocently enough, with the birth of the new reincarnation in a different hospital than you were born. You see your new parents, who are quite different than your old parents. Putting your thoughts aside, you continue watching as see your incarnation grow up throughout the years.

You see them grow up to be a teenager, and you see them become more and more distant from their family. Soon, the screen grows dark, and you realize that you will soon watch the next life of the newest reincarnation. Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

The story begins with a young man named Riku, who lives in a world where magic has long been forgotten.

constraints.suffix:
Landro by his grandfather Frezna, a wizard, and has always dreamed of becoming a great wizard himself.  Riku didn't know what had ever happened to his parents; his grandfather refused to tell him.  He lived a lonely, isolated life and longed for a family outside his grandfather.  There were no photographs of his parents; the only picture was of a woman.  Sometimes he would see his grandfather gazing at the photograph, a wistful look on his face.  

His grandfather spent years training him, but it takes a long, long time to learn everything one needs to know to use magic to its full extent.  When Riku was 14, his grandfather passed away.  Riku had been kept at home his whole life and knew little about the world, but now he had to set out and find his way.  He decided to go to the city of Faltra, where he had heard from his grandfather that there were many people who could teach him about magic.

Riku's first day in Faltra is a disaster.  They spoke a different dialect than he had learned growing up, so it was very difficult to get around.  He did have a little money and was finally able to find a room to rent.  He knew he needed to find a job, and find someone to continue teaching him magic.  Over the next few weeks, he learned the dialect and started to find his way around the city.  He got a job at a bakery, where he worked hard and met a lot of people as he waited on them.  He made friends with a young girl named Selphie, who was a waitress at the bakery.  They became friends immediately, and it was almost like they had known one another forever.

One day, Selphie invited Riku to come to her house for dinner.  Selphie lived with her grandmother. He arrived with some flowers he had picked.  When he knocked on the door, an elderly woman opened it.  Riku stood in the doorway, frozen solid.  It was an older version of the woman in the photograph that his grandfather had.  Riku knew it had to be her; he too had spent hours looking at that photograph.  The woman also stood very still, staring at him.

"Riku," she said.  "Is it you?"

"Have we met?" Riku asked?

"Have you come here from Landro?"

"Yes," Riku said.

"Is Frezna your grandfather,"

"Yes," Riku responded.

"Where is he?"

"He died, and I came to Faltra to find someone to continue my magic education."

The woman motioned him inside, and sat heavily on the sofa, tears running down her face.  She told Riku she was his grandmother, and when his parent were killed by magic hunters, she and her husband had each taken one of the children and fled to keep them safe and keep teaching them magic.  Selphie was his sister!  By this point, she had joined them in the parlor and they both listed to the story their grandmother told.  She was teaching Selphie magic, but neither Riku nor Selphie's magic would be strong until they were reunited, as they were twins.  She hadn't known that her husband had passed away.  They hadn't seen each other in nearly 12 years, but had kept in touch as best they could.  

Riku and Selphie were overjoyed to be reunited, and they spent the evening talking and catching up. Riku and Selphie spent the next year honing their magic and making plans for how to use their powers to return Mana to its past glory.  That would be their next adventure.

JFK has no idea what you're talking about, and he's a little offended that you'd think he'd pull a prank like that. "I didn't send you a letter, Barack." 

"Well, I have it right here on my bedside table." JFK asks you to read it aloud to him. 

"Well, it says 'I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below." 

JFK is a little creeped out that someone would be impersonating him. "Well, why don't you call the number and see what happens?"

You decide to do a three-way call so that JFK can hear the conversation.

25ad6925dd65422989e3659250ac9bfd.infix: had no idea who sent you that letter and swore to you that it wasn't him. You ask JFK what's going on, since

You have no idea what to think of the situation. You ask JFK to explain the contents of the letter and the man who answered your call responds, "It's a job offer to come be my personal chef." 

"But I'm retired," you say. "Plus, I don't know how to cook. You know that, ever since I tried hosting that dinner party the one time and everyone got food poisoning."

The man who answered your call has no idea what you're talking about, even though JFK was certainly a guest at the dinner party you are referencing and most certainly must remember the horrible food poisoning he got from eating your attempt at roasted chicken with a side of mashed potatoes.

Suddenly, you realize what must be going on. You must be living in parallel time zones or parallel worlds, because JFK is in one world and the man who answered your call is in another, even though both of these men are JFK. The theory is a little wonky but quite frankly, you're not sure what else to think. There is no other good explanation for these circumstances. The man who answered your call must have offered you the job as a chef because he doesn't realize, as the real JFK should realize, how bad your cooking skills are. 

You feel a little weird that you must have your feet straddling two different time periods, but you decide to go with it. I mean, you've seen weirder things while living in the White House. The alien is a bit of a fanboy, and is trying to get Matt Damon to sign his autograph book.  However, every time the alien takes human form and tries to get close to Matt, the alien either gets lost in a crowd and is ignored, or is stopped by security.  

Eventually, the alien resorts to extreme measures, and simply sucks Matt Damon up into his spaceship on a beam of light.  

Matt Damon is terrified and confused, but the alien quickly explains that he is merely a huge fan, and just wants an autograph.   

Matt Damon is not convinced, and the alien is forced to take Matt Damon to his home planet to prove that he is actually an alien, and not a crazed kidnapper who has built a hovercraft and disguised it as a spaceship.

The alien is nonplussed, but agrees to travel across the universe with his favorite actor. 

The alien takes Matt Damon to his home planet, which is a barren wasteland, and explains that the planet was once beautiful, but the evil invaders wiped out most of the native aliens and destroyed all of the crops.

eabc1c5c071c494ca5b65a3262ed7bbc.infix: to know how he can help, using his star power on Earth and his reputation as

constraints.suffix:

So the alien then shows Matt Damon his collection of Matt Damon memorabilia, including a Matt Damon action figure, a Matt Damon lunchbox, and all of Matt Damon's movies on a kind of foreign recording medium that works in outer space without electricity.

Matt Damon, being a celebrity, quickly forgets all about the famine and the invaders, and ends up basking in the admiration of yet another adoring fan.  

In fact, Matt thinks, he could make a fortune if the studios recognize all of the revenue that his movies are earning outside of Earth, so he asks for a tour of the planet, where he can meet more fans.

The alien shows Matt Damon around, and a few of the locals are thrilled to see him, but most of them just ignore him.  It turns out, that Matt Damon only has a few fans outside of the solar system, and only one of them has even watched his movies.  

Matt is disappointed, but he at least figures that he could get inspiration for a new movie from what he sees, so he asks to go to the library to learn more about the invaders.

The alien takes Matt Damon to the library, and Matt Damon is shocked to see that the library is a tiny, one-room building with a single display screen in it.

On that screen, Matt instantly watches the entire history of this planet, and all of his questions are answered.  

He asks to return to Earth, and even invites the alien to stay with him in Los Angeles.

The alien, however, refuses.

As much as he loves Matt Damon, the alien admits, he would rather live in a barren wasteland where his life is in constant danger, than have to live on the same planet as Ben Affleck


THE END

has done many great things for humanity such as his work helping to feed the hungry. This of course pushes us to help him whenever something bad happens because we treat him like our own. The usual extraction team sets off into space to infiltrate the alien ship and take him back. When the team gets on board, they encounter all kinds of alien security and must use their own methods to get through. There are many new traps and a couple of soldiers get killed pretty quickly because of them. It becomes a matter of preserving the rest of the team at one point since there were very few left. 

Finally, they locate Matt in the secure ritual chamber where they are preparing to extract his brain matter. They have to fight their way down the long hallway filled with alien soldiers and traps. It becomes apparent that they may not survive this encounter. It is a hard-fought battle, but in the end, they make it to Matt. They release him from the shackles and begin to look for an exit. All of a sudden, a massive security robot shows up with flamethrowers. It is the "biggest and baddest" robot they have ever encountered. The captain instructs the team to run the other way and they do end up finding a ventilation shaft to escape through. It becomes appareet if they let Matt be taken again there may not be another chance to rescue him. He is worth too much to humanity and the devastation that would follow his capture would be unimaginable.

The team flies home and celebrates the victory with a grain of salt. They explain to the president that they must get Matt into a maximum-security safe house so this does not happen again. The president agrees and they begin to prepare for his transport. Matt is sad about the news but realizes there is no other way until all the aliens are killed. The team goes to see him off and wishes him luck, Matt thanks them for the help and says he will never forget them. The president orders a nuclear strike on the alien ship so Matt can finally be safe. They evade the strike and disappear into the darkness of space. Matt will never be safe and humanity will always worry. This is a hero's life.

An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing. They ’ve put together an elite team, comprised of the best mercenaries our planet has to offer. These men will stop at nothing to bring Matt Damon home, dead or alive. As it turns out, some of them even prefer bringing him back dead. They're motivated by greed, and not so much the desire to get Matt Damon for themselves, but to make sure no one else can have him.

In the meantime, our alien has taken Matt Damon on a wild ride through the solar system, showing him

constraints.suffix:
the wonders of the stars. The kidnapping wasn't motived by profit or a desire to possess, it turns out that the alien is a huge fan of Matt Damon, and was simply too shy to introduce himself. The two have become fast friends, and Matt Damon has forgotten that he was ever even kidnapped in the first place. They go to Mars, and dine with the Martians, and have a grand old time. They travel to Venus, and Matt Damon and the alien go into the jungle on a hair (and antenna) raising excursion to bag a Venusian tiger. Next they hit up Saturn, and Matt Damon is stunned by the lovely rings, as well as the fact that they've come so close to terraforming them. As it turns out, all of the planets of the solar system are inhabited by intelligent life, and in fact, they're all a lot nicer than Earth.

But even though Matt Damon has forgotten about Earth, Earth has not forgotten about Matt Damon. The mercenary ship is launched, and begins its slow crawl through the solar system to retrieve the wayward actor. They finally catch up with the actor and his new best friend on Pluto, where Matt Damon and the alien are just hanging out by a pool. They try to 'rescue' Matt Damon, and the alien defends him by hurling his body forward at the mercenaries. They open fire, and the alien is blown to pieces. Enraged and crazy with grief, Matt Damon seizes one of the mercenaries' guns and  attacks the killers, who are not expecting this kind of resistance from the  seemingly ineffectual Hollywood star.

Single-handedly, he manages to take out the whole squad of mercenaries, and then realizes that the alien was the love of his life, and is gone forever, thanks to Earth. He broods for awhile, then arms himself and boards the alien ship. He spends the rest of his life on a mission, to destroy the Earth, and all of its people, and he won't rest until he, or humanity, are no more.

e34e7611bef74a0aafda89752af534f3.prefix:
For John, he had a fairly uneventful life. He had a fulfliling job, a stable family, and he had plenty of money and time to pursue his hobbies and interests. It would appear that nothing too major would affect him in his life, but that was not the case. For John experienced the oddest event one day, one that would bring about adversity in his life.

His children had gifted him a mug last Father's day, which he cherished and used every day for his morning tea. He liked to drink it to relax before work, and his children were happy whenever they saw him use the mug they bought for him. However, one day they woke up and looked at him funny while he was drinking his tea.

"You get a new mug Dad?" asked his daughter, who was at the time only four years old. Puzzled, John replied no. For it was the same mug he drank from every day since last Father's day, a step-up from the plain ceramic mug he used to

constraints.suffix:
mug around, he noted that his children were indeed correct, the mug he held did not say #1 Dad. In fact it said, #54 Dad. Thinking it was an elaborate prank from his family, John asked his children where his old mug was. They all shrugged their shoulders and said they didn't know. Asking his wife who was heading to work, she seemed as confused as he was regarding the mug, and denied any involvement in the different appearance of the mug.

In any case, John placed the mug in the sink, and would come back to clean it later. He dropped off his kids at school, and returned back home to get to work. Work went on as normal, but when he went to get his mug from the sink he noticed something bizarre. The mug he placed in the sink now said #50 Dad. It dropped down by 4 numbers, he was sure of it. Growing more confused, he thought someone had broken into his house, but he had found no signs of forced entry, and his mug was in the same place he had set it down. Grabbing the mug, he took a picture of it, and made a post online about how odd it was for his mug to say such a thing. Most applauded him for buying such a novel mug, and did not give his incident any further thought.

However, the next day the mug would now say #65 Dad. Like before, John posted the same picture, and people were again amused by the novelty of such a mug. Some even mentioning he had dropped several ranks down, and asked what he did to become worse than he was before.

The following days would be the same type of incidents. He would post the mug with his new rank, which sometimes did not change at all and on other days were fairly different than the day before. He become well known as the man with the changing mug, and people were genuinely interested in the mug, and the reason for it's weirdness. Others were skeptical, and claimed John had multiple mugs made, but his friends and family all supported John, and noted he had quite few mugs stored in his house, with most of them being blank. For the remainder of his life, John had become well known to others not for his notoriety or prestige from his actions or efforts, nor from his job and or position in life. He was known for his novel ceramic mug, which reflected his rank in the world, and showed others that indeed someone or some force was ranking all the dads in the world, and maybe there was a way to measure how good a father a person can really be.

The Americans were surprised that they were the only ones who maintained strict isolation.    The Russians were busy taking up all of Europe, and the Chinese had already colonized Africa.  While America was isolated, they were able to focus on becoming independent from other nations.  They weren't dependent on any fuel sources from other nations.  In fact, they had developed a new

constraints.suffix:
was a block of solid fuel that could be used as a power source for anything from cars to spaceships.  The fuel was very easy to transfer and manufacture.

A single drop of hadronium allowed the average car driver to drive for one year.  The outside word seemed to still be utilizing fossil fuels.  That is the primary reason why the Chinese had colonized Africa.  While the Americans were isolated, they had no contact with the Canadians.  It seemed that climate change had thawed out many of the cold areas of Canada.   They had access to more land than they did before.

Due to economic instability and other factors plaguing the countries of the world, an agreement was made for each country to go into isolation, for the next 100 years. This means that the countries will not be able to travel outside of their borders, nor communicate with other nations. This was approved by many if not most of the nations of the world, and was backed up by countless experts who agreed that isolation was needed for the world to stabilize itself. With the approval of the world's leaders, the countries of the world entered isolation on the year 2101, remaining isolated from others until the year 2102.

Within the first year, all forms of communication were cut off, and the only way to communicate was through a network of satellites set up across nations in case of a severe emergency, that required the intervention of other countries to aid one another. However, the satellites were never utilized in the hundred of years of isolation. In fact, it appeared as if most countries were fine during isolation, able to recover economically and become stable as experts had predicted. There were

The year 2112 eventually arrived, and communications between countries were re-established. However, it was soon discovered that there were major issues that had arisen in the absence of communication and trade throughout the world. Many of the third-world countries had been able to make due during the isolation, but the first-world countries had suffered from the lack of trade, in addition to other economic issues. These countries for whatever reason it may be did not chose to use the satellite communication during the period of isolation, out of pride and fear that the other countries would view them as vulnerable. This was proven to be a fatal mistake, as these countries were not prepared for the monumental challenges that they faced in the return of communication. Many of the countries that suffered from isolation ended up going into conflicts with one another, for resources and other material goods that it had lacked during the isolation. Trade battles and other economic struggles occurred between the biggest nations of the world, dragging the smaller countries into it causing them to suffer as well. It turns out that isolation was not the answer to the world's problems, and that the only way for nations to survive was continue to communicate and work with one another. The President of the United States was sitting in his office, reading a book when the technicians brought in the device. A gift from England to the US "our old friends" according the the communication. It was a communication device, one that allowed video calls with crystal clarity. He was told it was much better than the old tech, and that stung. What was to come stung even more. 

"Mr. President, we have a call for you from the Prime Minister of England." The President of the US answered, and the conversation that followed devastated him. He learned just how far behind they were, just how little they understood of the current situation, and worst of all, just how little the US mattered in the world now. It had moved on without them, and while the other nations didn't mind the US being back, they didn't really care either way to be honest.

The call over, the President sat back in his chair. "Well, that was a real kick in the teeth." He called in his cabinet, and they discussed what to do next, what they should tell the citizens. 

The next day, the President addressed the nation. "Fellow Americans, I have some news that may be hard to hear. But I believe you are ready for it..." 

They might not have been ready for it. But it was happening ready or not. And that, my friends is the end of this story, and the beginning of the next.

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. I always told her that I would be fine, but deep down I was terrified. I stayed in doors as much as I could in my first two years of college, quickly running from building to building in order to avoid any bees. I always wore long sleeves and pants, even in the summer, in order to avoid any stings. My friends never questioned my actions and accepted me for who I was. My junior year of college, I decided to take a summer job in the city. My summer job was being a waitress at a hotel spa/pool. I had to serve customers inside of the hotel, but on occasion, I would need to go outside by the pool. One day, I met a nice boy out by the pool

constraints.suffix: we got to talking about school. I was so engrossed by our talk, that I forgot I was spending too much time outdoors. I was sitting on a lounge chair by the pool when I felt a bee land on my shoulder. The boy I had met told me I had a bee on my shoulder and I was paralyzed with fear, running back inside, hoping the bee would fly away. I got back inside the hotel and discovered that the bee had remained on my shoulder. I was about to swat the bee off my shoulder, when suddenly, I hear the bee say, "Your Majesty, what are your orders? I could not believe my ears, I thought I might be hallucinating from a bee sting. I looked around and saw that no one else was in the room, so I decided to ask the bee a question. "Did you call me Majesty?", I said to the bee. "Yes, I am your Majesty's personal bee." I told the bee that my mother had always told me that I had a deadly allergy to bees, so I lived in fear of bees. The bee told me that I did not have a deadly allergy, and that my mother had lied to me. I wondered why my mother would lie to me about something so strange. The bee told me that my mother had lied to me because she was a bee queen, and she wanted to protect me from her enemies. I asked the bee who my enemies were and the bee said that my enemies were the wasps. I had never heard of wasps, so I asked the bee what they were. The bee said that wasps were the ancient enemies of bees, caught in a long war throughout the centuries. The bee told me that I was the princess bee, and that I was the only one who could end the war between bees and wasps. I asked the bee what the first order of business was in the war against the wasps. The bee told me that the first order of business was to find the wasps' queen. The wasp queen had been living in Europe, all the way across the world from my home. I told the bee that I would go to Europe to find the wasp queen. I told my mother I had to do my job as the princess bee and stop the longstanding war. My mother told me that the war had been going on for so long, that it was pointless to stop it. We sat at her table and she told me that she had been waiting for me to come and stop the war. She had been the leader of the wasps for far too long and had seen many casualties. My mother, the wasp queen and myself agreed to end the war and we signed a peace treaty. The treaty also established a partnership between bees and wasps, so that we could work together and build a better world. I was so happy to have ended the war that I hugged my mother and the wasp queen. My mother and I left Germany and flew back home, knowing that our future looked bright. When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

I thought that there was a lot of hubub on the news, but I didn't know what it was all about until I sat down to really pay attention. "It's a tragedy!" the newscaster was gasping. "The government has been hiding the side effects of the immortality drug for decades!" I settled into my seat, feeling my knees creak and hearing my joints audibly pop. I winced. I'd always half felt sorry for myself that I was too old for the drug, but the other half of me knew, just knew that the other shoe would drop some day. I sighed and adjusted my pillow behind my aching back as I turned up the volume to listen. My ear weren't what they used to be.

"They're pulling the drug immediately!" the newscaster was almost shrieking, and I could see her panic. "They say the effects of the drug will wear off exactly 58 years after they were first administeded!" I could see the shock and disbelief of her terrifically youthful face. "We're all going to get...old!" She could barely get the word out. Like it was a curse. I felt a twinge of pity for her. Here I'd had my whole like to settle into myself and
bc89dc4ac2a04f3aae685f619bb0fd24.infix: get used to the aches and pains, to get comfortable with the notion of my own mortality. These younger people who had lived their whole lives feeling immortal They were about

to hit a hard reality.

I turned off the TV and settled back into my chair. This would change everything, I realized. There would be repercussions all through society. People who had put off having kids because they had all the time in the world suddenly had no time. There weren't many kids around, I realized. The world could be in for a whole lot of trouble if its whole work force suddenly aged out of their ablilty to work. My dawning sense of dread was only slightly assuaged by the fact that I was too old to really feel the repercussions of this. I'd be dead before it really got bad. I pressed the button on my phone to call the assistant in my home. I loved it here, I mused, as I waited for her to respond. This retirement community was the perfect place to hide out and live my last decade or two in peace. I pushed the button again. And again. Finally I called the front desk. A harried voice answered. 

"Is it an emergency?" the woman squawked at me, "You should call the police if it is. Nobody's coming! Everyone left!" I sat up. "What did you say?" The dread was spreading through me like a nagging fever in my bones. "They left!" She repeated. "They all realized they don't have much time left to be young; nobody wanted to be stuck here for the last good year they have left!"

"But you're still here," I tried to argue, although I heard the wavering in my own voice. 

"I'll be outta here as soon as I find my purse," she said distractedly. "Sorry, pal. You're on your own."

And then I realized that everything was about to change for the worse, and not just for the fools who tried to make themselves young forever.   I was about to be alone. For the rest of my life. However long it would be.

111ee57118054cc6b8fa4ef98c1a3408.prefix:
When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

By then, the world is almost entirely filled with bright-eyed, attractive, youthful young adults. People like you have to hide on the edges of society, avoiding their judgemental gazes at all costs as you become more and more decrepit and they remain strikingly beautiful.

Because of that, you don't even hear about the breakthrough discovery until weeks after it's become a global sensation. The first time you hear about it, you're in the
111ee57118054cc6b8fa4ef98c1a3408.infix: middle of a crowd of young adults waiting to get into the

constraints.suffix:
grocery store.

A girl in front of you in the line spots you and grabs you by the shoulders.

"You're one of the lucky ones," she weeps, nearly knocking you off your feet with her youthful strength. "You're one of the Lost Generations, aren't you?"

It's silly that she needs to ask, because it's obvious. But you nod anyways.

Her tears fall faster. "Please remember me," she sobs, flinging herself into your arms and squeezing your shoulders in a tight embrace. "Remember all of us when we... when we..."

Her words choke to a halt, leaving you baffled and afraid.

A young man approaches you and places his hand on her back. He also looks sad.

"We're sorry," he says to you. "For all the times people like us... well. We didn't know, of course. And we never got the choice, did we? People like us... this is the end of the line, isn't it?"

You don't know what to say. You have no idea what they're talking about. So you nod, hoping it might mean something to them.

Sniffling, the girl detaches from you and takes the young man's hand. "Please remember us," she repeats, giving you one last mournful stare before stepping through the store door.

As the automated door shuts behind her, you realize it's covered in a large poster, marked with the seal of the government. It's a warning about the side effects of the immortality drug.

You read the poster, and the world falls out from under you.

"Due to the violent development of suicidal-homocidal tendencies in adults who have received anti-ageing treatment, we ask that all members of the affected population (ages 26-83) turn themselves in for containment and voluntary destruction. This facility has been marked as a designated internment location. Groceries for youths and members of the Lost Generations can be found down the road at the convention center."

When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

Dan woke up early that morning, as usual, had his cup of coffee, like usual, and sat down to watch the morning news, as usual. Everything was as it always was. To be honest, he was beginning to be okay with the fact that he would die someday - it wasn't the bitter disappointment is was almost 60 years ago. 

But then the morning was "as usual" anymore. 

Dan was watching the news when the anchorwoman, a young woman who had been with the station for about a year, suddenly froze. She looked about 22, the age most people got the drug, though some got it as early as 16. She was frozen in place, her eyes wide and her mouth slightly open. Staring at the paper and then the teleprompter in front of her. She finally

constraints.suffix:
sorry, we have breaking news." Last month the earliest recipients of the drug 4EvR all reported to medical centers complaining of headaches. Within 6 hours they had lost their vision and hearing. Within 24 hours they seemed to be comatose, though brain scans showed the same activity levels as a normal, conscious person. They remain in that state."

Dan stared at the screen in shock. The newscaster continued. "Scientists have been studying their condition and have come to the conclusion that it is due to the drug 4EvR." She began to cry, "And according to their findings it is not only an inevitable side effect, but also one that is triggered or transmitted to users. To summarize, all people who have ever taken 4EvR will almost certainly have been exposed to others who have been exposed to the original group and we should all expect to experience the same side effects within 2 weeks at the most." 

Dan turned off the TV. He was in shock. He had never taken the drug missing the age cut off by a mere two years, but all of his younger relatives had. His children, his grandchildren, so many others. Ans soon they would essentially be helpless with only a few aged people like himself to take care of them. 

Dan was suddenly filled with rage. It wasn't fair. He had had expectations, and now everything was upside down. This was not his problem to deal with. He sat at his desk, and shaking, wrote notes to all his loved ones. He wrote a note to his children, telling them how much he loved them, and how he was sorry that he couldn't be there to help them. And then he went upstairs, and found the bottle of pills, the same ones his wife had used a few years ago when she just got tired of being old in a young world. And he took many more than needed. And left the world before everyone, just like he always thought he would.

age.   If you don't, you'll die anyway. You decide to take the drug. 

One week after taking the drug, I have survived. I have been

constraints.suffix:
given a second chance at life. I have been given a second chance to make the world a better place. I set out to find ways to make a difference in the world. I have decided to use my time to help the world. Just then, there's a knock at the door. I open the door and there is a man standing there. He tells me that he is here to take me to the government. "I don't have an appointment with the government."

"No," the man says. "You work there now." 

"What?" I ask.

"When you took the drug, you consented to 5 years of service. Didn't you read the form?" 

"I don't remember signing a form."

The man sighs. "You were given a form when you took the drug. Look, I don't have time to get into legal stuff with you. I'm just your driver. We gotta go."

I sighed. Well, I wanted to make a difference. Let's get to work, I thought. I grabbed my coat and followed the man to the car. Once I was buckled in, I asked, "So, what's my job?" 

The man said nothing. He just started the car and drove away.

"I didn't bring a lunch or anything. Will there be a cafeteria there? At work?" I asked.

Again, the man said nothing. 



The man drove for hours. We were in the middle of nowhere. Finally, we arrived at a building. The man led me inside and we walked down a long hallway. He stopped at a door and opened it. When he opened it, I saw a man standing there in a suit. Not just any man. It was the President. "Welcome to the government," he said. "And welcome to your first day at work." 

"What is my job?" I asked.

"This is your job. My job." he said. "You are now the President of the United States."

"Why me?" 

"You're the only one who can do this job. We chose you out of many. We think you are ready. Welcome aboard, Mrs. President."

When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

You are seated at the head of a table in a crowded conference room. A man is speaking to you. He is a film director, and he has a movie he wants to make. He says he wants to make a movie of your next life.

"Just wait a minute," you say, "I am watching your movie right now."

"That's because must have agreed to make it and you are watching the result," he says.

"I don't remember agreeing to make a movie of my next life," you say. "Of course not," replied the man, " that is not how these things work."

"How do they work?" you ask.

"Your brain is erased between lives," says the man. "Therefore, you don't remember making the movie."

"But this is supposed to be my future, not my past," you say.

"It is your future," says the man, "but it is also your past."

"How can that be?," you reply.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

The story begins with a young man named Riku, who lives in a world where magic has long been forgotten. He has been raised in Landro by his grandfather Frezna, a wizard, and has always dreamed of becoming a great wizard himself.  Riku didn't know what had ever happened to his parents; his grandfather refused to tell him.  He lived a lonely, isolated life and longed for a family outside his grandfather.  There were no photographs of his parents; the only picture was of a woman.  Sometimes he would see his grandfather gazing at the photograph, a wistful look on his face.  

His grandfather spent years training him, but it takes a long, long time to learn everything one needs to know to use magic to its full extent.  When Riku was 14, his grandfather passed away.  Riku had been kept at home his whole life and knew little about the world, but now he had to set out and find his way.  He decided to go to the city of Faltra, where he had heard from his grandfather that there were many people who could teach him about magic.

Riku's first day in Faltra is a disaster.  They spoke a different dialect than he had learned growing up, so it was very difficult to get around.  He did have a little money and was finally able to find a room to rent.  He knew he needed to find a job, and find someone to continue teaching him magic.  Over the next few weeks, he learned the dialect and started to find his way around the city.  He got a job at a bakery, where he worked hard and met a lot of people as he waited on them.  He made friends with a young girl named Selphie, who was a waitress at the bakery.  They became friends immediately, and it was almost like they had known one another forever.

An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

For the third time this year, Matt Damon was missing. A few months back the last time this happened, the entire world basically stopped and searched for him. Come to find out he fell asleep on his yacht and floated out into the middle of the Pacific ocean for three months. So of course, when he disappeared this time, the entire world searched for him again. They checked the oceans and the coffee bars as well as small indigenous villages in South America where someone could go and just be out of the public eye for a while.  After three months of searching, not a single lead was found. Then the big break came. NASA scientists discovered a tracking anomaly about the time that Damon went missing in the same area that he had last been seen. The anomaly was very interesting in that it appeared to be traveling at a speed that would take it all the way into outer space. After a few days of intense investigation from looking at radar images to doorbell cameras their worst fears were realized. Matt Damon had been kidnapped by aliens.

"So why would they kidnap Matt Damon?" asked the president. That was the question everyone else was asking, too. So NASA set up a broadcast to beam into space to see if we could get an answer.

You were in general scared of getting hurt, whether it was from being stung from a bee, or from getting hurt from tripping on the grass. Although you were happy to see them, you could not ease your fears completely nor calm your nerves. You still tried to play with them, having the occasional fun while playing kick ball with them. As hours pass, your friends and their parents all go home, leaving you with your parents in the park. There were others there, but you did not know them, nor did you want to go near them. Your parents suggest you should play a bit more in the park, before heading on back home. You reluctantly agree, and head back to play in the grass. "Hey there, little one," the voice calmly states, although you are not sure where it comes from.

You turn and look around, thinking it was an adult that was speaking to you nearby.

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. I always told her that I would be fine, but deep down I was terrified. I stayed in doors as much as I could in my first two years of college, quickly running from building to building in order to avoid any bees. I always wore long sleeves and pants, even in the summer, in order to avoid any stings. My friends never questioned my actions and accepted me for who I was. My junior year of college, I decided to take a summer job in the city. My summer job was being a waitress at a hotel spa/pool. I had to serve customers inside of the hotel, but on occasion, I would need to go outside by the pool. One day, I met a nice boy out by the pool and we got to talking about school.

When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen. As your next life unfolds, you experience all kinds of emotions. You laugh and cry at so many scenes, you watch them go by with no accounting for time. You have no idea how much time is passing. You can't feel it and there is no timekeeping mechanism on display, anywhere in the theater. You are just watching your next life, and you are watching it unfold in real time.

It feels so odd to watch day turn to night, and months pass, on screen. You don't feel bored and you have no concept of time passing, in your space. You wonder how all of this is possible? How
b43dca37a1704c10990f320c35f2828f.infix: can you be watching your next life, in real time, and how can you be watching it

constraints.suffix:
in a theater, with other people who look just like you? These questions are huge. You decide to ask one of the other audience members, a woman sitting right next to you. She shrugs her shoulders and speaks, but you don't understand the language. You return the shrug, but don't bother speaking. 

You look back at the screen, and you see your next life unfold. You see every mistake that you make in your next life. You want so badly to tell your next self not to make so many mistakes, but you are powerless to do so. You don't understand the point of this exercise. You feel like you are watching a movie, and you are powerless to change the outcome. This all seems like some kind of sick joke.

You look around the theater and wonder if some of them may speak English, your native tongue (at least in the life that you lived). It's impossible to tell. They all look just like you, men and women alike. You wonder if they are your previous reincarnations, and you wonder how many of them are watching their next life, in this theater.

You know that you are connected to these other beings, by appearance alone, but you don't understand the point of being here with them, if you can't communicate to them. You don't understand why you are watching this film of your next life, if you are powerless to intervene. You want to ask someone, but you don't know who to ask. The questions begin to form in your mind, you have specific ideas on how to improve things but can't say them in a language that your fellow audience members will understand. Suddenly, you have a very specific question on the tip of your mind. You notice that others are looking at you, and suddenly you realize that they can communicate with you telepathically. They are offering suggestions and ideas, based on your concentrated thought. 

You ask your question, and they answer. You begin to realize that the person on the screen is another incarnation of all of you. When one of you asks a pointed question, and everyone else answers, somehow the person on the screen gets the same thoughts. Now it makes sense. You are all connected, and you are all watching your next life unfold, in real time.  This is the evolution of your being and you finally understand life, and death.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

Humans are now discovering that they have the power to travel back in time.  This has become true for one man in particular, Bob.  Bob didn't realize he had this power until the day that he lost his favorite sunglasses.  But when he slips back to the day where he first found them, something unexpected happens.  He couldn't figure out how to come back to the present time.  Traveling through time was such a new power for humans that he didn't know what to do.  He sat on a nearby bench after putting on his newly found sunglasses to think about it for a bit.

"Do you have any idea what time it is?" he asked a passerby.
"It is time for you to go home," she replied.
Bob was confused. He wanted to get home.  But just then, a though popped into his head.  Maybe, just maybe, that was a clue for him to be able to find his way back to the present

at the time. So off he went for the short walk to his house in the small neighborhood just outside of the city.

Coming back to his house, Bob was confused as to why he was supposed to come here. Everything looked the same and he didn't know what to do to get back to the present time.  All Bob wanted to do was get his sunglasses and it has turned into a daylong adventure!  

Bob began to walk from room to room in his house to search for a clue on how to get back to the present time. As he walked through the kitchen, he noticed a strange looking plant.  Bob didn't own any plants so he thought it was odd that it was there.  It was the only thing out of place.  

"I don't know why but I think that plant has something to do with me getting back to the present time," Bob thought. He began to inspect the plant further.  It seemed to have some sort of small berries on it.  They were purple, looked plump and round, and smelled delicious.  Bob was so curious about the plant that he decided to pick one of the berries and take a bite.

Bob started to feel very tired within seconds of ingesting the mysterious berry.  He was now regretting this decision.  He collapsed on the kitchen floor.  He was unable to do anything as he drifted off into an odd dream. When he awoke, he was in the same spot in the kitchen.  However, the mysterious plant had disappeared.  Bob was surprised that he had returned to the present time. "I discovered the key to time travel and didn't even know it," Bob said to himself.  From that time on, Bob regularly enjoyed traveling through time now that he knew how to get back home.

He has been raised in Landro by his grandfather Frezna, a wizard, and has always dreamed of becoming a great wizard himself.  Riku didn't know what had ever happened to his parents; his grandfather refused to tell him.  He lived a lonely, isolated life and longed for a family outside his grandfather.  There were no photographs of his parents; the only picture was of a woman.  Sometimes he would see his grandfather gazing at the photograph, a wistful look on his face.

Riku's first day in Faltra is a disaster.  They spoke a different dialect than he had learned growing up, so it was very difficult to get around.  He did have a little money and was finally able to find a room to rent.  He knew he needed to find a job, and find someone to continue teaching him magic.  Over the next few weeks, he learned the dialect and started to find his way around the city.  He got a job at a bakery, where he worked hard and met a lot of people as he waited on them.  He made friends with a young girl named Selphie, who was a waitress at the bakery.  They became friends immediately, and it was almost like they had known one another forever.

One day, Selphie invited Riku to come to her house for dinner.  Selphie lived with her grandmother. He arrived with some flowers he had picked.  When he knocked on the door, an elderly woman opened it.  Riku stood in the doorway, frozen solid.  It was an older version of the woman in the photograph that his grandfather had.  Riku knew it had to be her; he too had spent hours looking at that photograph.  The woman also stood very still, staring at him.

"Riku," she said.  "Is it you?"

"Have we met?" Riku asked?

"Have you come here from Landro?"

"Yes," Riku said.

"Is Frezna your grandfather,"

"Yes," Riku responded.

"Where is he?"

"He died, and I came to Faltra to find someone to continue my magic education."

The woman motioned him inside, and sat heavily on the sofa, tears running down her face.  She told Riku she was his grandmother, and when his parent were killed by magic hunters, she and her husband had each taken one of the children and fled to keep them safe and keep teaching them magic.  Selphie was his sister!  By this point, she had joined them in the parlor and they both listed to the story their grandmother told. You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK." You know what JFK means. It's a secret code that you heard when you were President. A code that needs to be activated only in cases of the utmost urgency. You quickly call the number, horrified at what you will find out. A woman picks up. She sounds like someone at a call center because you can hear other people frantically talking all around her. 

"Mr. President, thank you for calling. It has happened and we need your help now." says the woman.

Scared and confused at the same time, you ask "What has happened?".

"Reality has shifted. Half of the people are now from another reality. We need your help." she says.

I agree to help and go to a specified location. Upon arriving I am sat in front of a desk and given a little dial which can be turned left or right. 

A mysterious man in a suit

constraints.suffix:
hands me a folder with the words "You're our last hope" on the cover.

I read it and it says that half of the people in our world are from another reality. It's part of what is called the Mandella effect. It says that this dial will decide which half of the population will be killed. We do not know which half is from the alternate reality and which is from our reality. This is for me to decide as part of the JFK project. 

If I turn the dial all the way to the right all of the people from that reality disappear. If I turn it to the left all the people from the other reality do. The man leaves the room and I am left to decide this for myself. 

What if I am wrong? We'll be a world filled with only people from another reality. Am I from another reality? Will I disappear as well?

I don't want to do it but I am familiar with the JFK project. I have to do it. I close my eyes, hoping I don't disappear and turn the dial to the left. Now there is only darkness and nothing more.

"I got this letter from you and I was just calling to make sure it wasn't a joke."

JFK has no idea what you're talking about, and he's a little offended that you'd think he'd pull a prank like that. "I didn't send you a letter, Barack." 

"Well, I have it right here on my bedside table." JFK asks you to read it aloud to him. 

"Well, it says 'I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below." 

JFK is a little creeped out that someone would be impersonating him. "Well, why don't you call the number and see what happens?"

You decide to do a three-way call so that JFK can hear the conversation. 

The phone rings once, twice, three times...and then a voice answers. As it turns out, the voice belongs to none other than John F. Kennedy. You're confused, because JFK just told you that he had no idea who sent you that letter and swore to you that it wasn't him. You ask JFK what's going on, since he is also on the line as a looped-in call participant.

"But I'm retired," you say. "Plus, I don't know how to cook. You know that, ever since I tried hosting that dinner party the one time and everyone got food poisoning."

The man who answered your call has no idea what you're talking about, even though JFK was certainly a guest at the dinner party you are referencing and most certainly must remember the horrible food poisoning he got from eating your attempt at roasted chicken with a side of mashed potatoes.

Suddenly, you realize what must be going on. The theory is a little wonky but quite frankly, you're not sure what else to think. There is no other good explanation for these circumstances. Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude." The 92nd little pig didn't care about the wolf's unsolicited opinion. The 92nd little pig was happy on his pile of uranium. 

Then one day, the wolf knocked on the door of the 92nd little pig. He was surprised that the wolf would come around, given his previous attitude. The wolf knocked and the 92nd little pig didn't play the game the first 3 little pigs had played.
f3f02425b9904e5b8084c47c1c6d2a42.infix: He opened the door, careless and without fear. The wolf did not eat him. He simply asked to come inside for a few minutes. The 92nd little pig let him

constraints.suffix:
in, because he was a polite pig and not the kind of person that would kick someone out in the middle of a story.

The wolf sat down and the pig served refreshments. They talked about the weather and their families. They slowly got to know one another and some trust had been built. At that point, the wolf made a confession to the pig. The wolf confided in the pig that he had been suffering from depression. He asked the 92nd little pig how he kept such a great attitude toward life, after having been dealt such a disappointing hand. 

The 92nd little pig told the wolf that he didn't always have this amazing outlook on life. He explained that, when he first moved into his little house on the hill of depleted uranium, he had felt defeated and saddened. He felt as depleted as that uranium his life was built upon. But then, one day, he had a revelation. He was looking at everything from the point of view that he was guaranteed some lot in life, that would resemble the lives of the first 3 little pigs. He was the 92nd little pig, and his life would be different. It would look different, but could be every bit as enjoyable and as great an adventure. He was determined to make a positive impact on the world, as well.

He had started doing some volunteer work at the pig hospital, where there were many little pigs that were much worse of than himself. He explained that this had given him the perspective that he needed to break out of his depression. The wolf listened thoughtfully and reached a kind of revelatios of his own. He had never done anything nice for anyone. He always ended up being the big bad wolf, when really he just wanted to be plain old wolf. 

The 92nd little pig invited the wolf to go with him to the hospital. The went together, to work for their community that day. They have been working together every since, and their story is even more famous now, among sick little pigs, that the story of the first 3 little pigs.

eabc1c5c071c494ca5b65a3262ed7bbc.prefix:
An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

The alien is a bit of a fanboy, and is trying to get Matt Damon to sign his autograph book.  However, every time the alien takes human form and tries to get close to Matt, the alien either gets lost in a crowd and is ignored, or is stopped by security.
eabc1c5c071c494ca5b65a3262ed7bbc.infix:
Eventually, the alien resorts to extreme measures, and simply sucks Matt Damon up into his spaceship on a beam of light.  

Matt Damon is

constraints.suffix:
terrified and confused, but the alien quickly explains that he is merely a huge fan, and just wants an autograph.   

Matt Damon is not convinced, and the alien is forced to take Matt Damon to his home planet to prove that he is actually an alien, and not a crazed kidnapper who has built a hovercraft and disguised it as a spaceship.

The alien is nonplussed, but agrees to travel across the universe with his favorite actor. 

The alien takes Matt Damon to his home planet, which is a barren wasteland, and explains that the planet was once beautiful, but the evil invaders wiped out most of the native aliens and destroyed all of the crops.  

Matt Damon is horrified, and he wants to know how he can help, using his star power on Earth and his reputation as a philanthropist.  

The alien, however, just wants to talk with his favorite celebrity, and not about the disappointing homeworld.   So the alien then shows Matt Damon his collection of Matt Damon memorabilia, including a Matt Damon action figure, a Matt Damon lunchbox, and all of Matt Damon's movies on a kind of foreign recording medium that works in outer space without electricity.

Matt Damon, being a celebrity, quickly forgets all about the famine and the invaders, and ends up basking in the admiration of yet another adoring fan.  

In fact, Matt thinks, he could make a fortune if the studios recognize all of the revenue that his movies are earning outside of Earth, so he asks for a tour of the planet, where he can meet more fans.

The alien shows Matt Damon around, and a few of the locals are thrilled to see him, but most of them just ignore him.  It turns out, that Matt Damon only has a few fans outside of the solar system, and only one of them has even watched his movies.  

Matt is disappointed, but he at least figures that he could get inspiration for a new movie from what he sees, so he asks to go to the library to learn more about the invaders.

The alien takes Matt Damon to the library, and Matt Damon is shocked to see that the library is a tiny, one-room building with a single display screen in it.

On that screen, Matt instantly watches the entire history of this planet, and all of his questions are answered.  

He asks to return to Earth, and even invites the alien to stay with him in Los Angeles.

The alien, however, refuses.

As much as he loves Matt Damon, the alien admits, he would rather live in a barren wasteland where his life is in constant danger, than have to live on the same planet as Ben Affleck


THE END

8024bf1914664591abe824dd583d2d2a.prefix:
An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

For the third time this year, Matt Damon was missing. A few months back the last time this happened, the entire world basically stopped and searched for him. Come to find out he fell asleep on his yacht and floated out into the middle of the Pacific ocean for three months. So of course, when he disappeared this time, the entire world searched for him again. They checked the oceans and the coffee bars as well as small indigenous villages in South America where someone could go and just be out of the public eye for a while.  After three months of searching, not a single lead was found. Then the big break came. NASA scientists discovered a tracking anomaly about the time that Damon went missing in the same area that he had last been seen. The anomaly was very interesting in that it appeared to be traveling at a speed that would take it all the way into outer space. After a few days of intense investigation from looking at radar images to doorbell cameras their worst fears were realized. Matt Damon had been kidnapped by aliens.

"So why would they kidnap Matt Damon?" asked the president. That was the question everyone

constraints.suffix:
NASA set up a broadcast to beam into space to see if we could get an answer. The message that was basically 'Anyone with any information on the abduction of an Earthling with a slight Bostonian accent and charming sneer, please contact us' was sent out between all of our satellites as far as we could beam it. The response was almost immediate. 'We have Matt Damon. We need to be entertained. You cannot have him back."

"We have to think of a plan," said the president, "but why do they need to be entertained?" Once again this question was on everyone's mind. All we wanted was Matt Damon back. Is there anyone else that could entertain these aliens? "Maybe we could ask the aliens to make a list of their favorite Earth entertainers," said the president. We could rotate them out like they were on tour. It would also keep the aliens from getting bored by the same actor.

Everyone agreed that this was a good idea and we started on our list of possible entertainers. There were several that actually volunteered. The list was narrowed down to twenty and sent to the aliens for their selections. They ended up trading Damon back to earth for a rotation of Bradley Cooper, Beyonce, and Celine Dion. The main thing was we had Matt Damon back. For now...

a0cc548fb40a4e22b1963674fb4b1f83.prefix:
An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing. For you see, Matt Damon is a famous actor, renowned for his many critically acclaimed works and acting roles. He is the star of the Bourne series, the star of the Ocean's series, and the star of many other movies. The aliens mistaking him for being the leader of mankind kidnapped him in order to weaken the military might of planet Earth, so they could conquer it much more easily. 

The aliens did not know that the military might of planet Earth is not based on the strength of one man, but on the strength of all the many countries and people that live on the planet. That is why, upon Matt Damon's kidnapping, all the true leaders of the world met up to discuss what to do about the aliens planning to conquer the planet. 

One of the Earth's leaders suggested an all out attack, while others chimed in that such an endeavor would likely fail if the aliens possessed superior technology. Others suggested more diplomatic options, wishing to converse with the alien leaders on finding a common ground or compromise. 

The final option was to send a single man to infiltrate the alien base, and rescue Matt Damon. That sole man would not only rescue
a0cc548fb40a4e22b1963674fb4b1f83.infix:
Matt Damon, but also set charges and explosives to destroy the alien base upon Matt Damon's rescue. 

The leaders of Earth agreed upon the final option, and sent the man to

constraints.suffix:
infiltrate the alien base. He was a secret, not officially registered as an agent of any country of the world. Trained since his youth to be the best stealth agent, he was supposedly a ghost in the field, not being heard or seen by enemy combatants. 
Beyond his skill, the man was given a special suit, that would allow him to blend in with his surroundings. This made his mission all to easy, as the aliens were found to not physically possess good eyesight or others senses to detect him. The stealth agent made his way through the base, eventually coming across Matt Damon.

"Oh thank god, someone's here to rescue me, replied Matt Damon. The man quietly nodded in response, and broke the lock to Damon's cell. Once freed, Matt Damon exited his cell and waited patiently for the man to discuss their next plan. 

"We need to get out of here, and blow up the base, the man whispered to Matt Damon.

Matt Damon was surprised, but agreed. They both went to the part of the base where all the munitions and space ships were located. The man set charges all around, including a special charge that would detonate a massive explosion, taking out the base and anyone that were in its blast radius.

They then sneaked back to the agent's ship, and flew away without ever being detected. Once a safe distance, the agent handed over the detonator to Matt Damon, giving him the honors of blowing up the base of the aliens.

Matt Damon humbly agreed to do so. With a massive explosion, the aliens were no more and humanity was saved.

For it was the efforts of both an unknown operative and Matt Damon who saved humanity from aliens, a tale that would soon be told on film by said actor.
