For John, he had a fairly uneventful life. He had a fulfliling job, a stable family, and he had plenty of money and time to pursue his hobbies and interests. It would appear that nothing too major would affect him in his life, but that was not the case. For John experienced the oddest event one day, one that would bring about adversity in his life.

His children had gifted him a mug last Father's day, which he cherished and used every day for his morning tea. He liked to drink it to relax before work, and his children were happy whenever they saw him use the mug they bought for him. However, one day they woke up and looked at him funny while he was drinking his tea.

"You get a new mug Dad?" asked his daughter, who was at the time only four years old. Puzzled, John replied no. For it was the same mug he drank from every day since last Father's day, a step-up from the plain ceramic mug he used to drink tea from.

Turning the mug around, he noted that his children were indeed correct, the mug he held did not say #1 Dad. In fact it said, #54 Dad. Thinking it was an elaborate prank from his family, John asked his children where his old mug was. They all shrugged their shoulders and said they didn't know. Asking his wife who was heading to work, she seemed as confused as he was regarding the mug, and denied any involvement in the different appearance of the mug.

In any case, John placed the mug in
e34e7611bef74a0aafda89752af534f3.infix: the sink, and would come back to clean it later. He dropped off his kids at school, and returned

constraints.suffix:
back home to get to work. Work went on as normal, but when he went to get his mug from the sink he noticed something bizarre. The mug he placed in the sink now said #50 Dad. It dropped down by 4 numbers, he was sure of it. Growing more confused, he thought someone had broken into his house, but he had found no signs of forced entry, and his mug was in the same place he had set it down. Grabbing the mug, he took a picture of it, and made a post online about how odd it was for his mug to say such a thing. Most applauded him for buying such a novel mug, and did not give his incident any further thought.

However, the next day the mug would now say #65 Dad. Like before, John posted the same picture, and people were again amused by the novelty of such a mug. Some even mentioning he had dropped several ranks down, and asked what he did to become worse than he was before.

The following days would be the same type of incidents. He would post the mug with his new rank, which sometimes did not change at all and on other days were fairly different than the day before. He become well known as the man with the changing mug, and people were genuinely interested in the mug, and the reason for it's weirdness. Others were skeptical, and claimed John had multiple mugs made, but his friends and family all supported John, and noted he had quite few mugs stored in his house, with most of them being blank. For the remainder of his life, John had become well known to others not for his notoriety or prestige from his actions or efforts, nor from his job and or position in life. He was known for his novel ceramic mug, which reflected his rank in the world, and showed others that indeed someone or some force was ranking all the dads in the world, and maybe there was a way to measure how good a father a person can really be.

the world entered isolation on the year 2101, remaining isolated from others until the year 2102.

Within the first year, all forms of communication were cut off, and the only way to communicate was through a network of satellites set up across nations in case of a severe emergency, that required the intervention of other countries to aid one another. However, the satellites were never utilized in the hundred of years of isolation. In fact, it appeared as if most countries were fine during isolation, able to recover economically and become stable as experts had predicted. There were no wars or conflicts, and the world continued to move on without major issues that would involve many nations around a singular issue. In fact, the only thing that seemed to really be a problem was that international trade was basically nonexistent. As per the rules of isolation, many countries were prohibited from trading with other countries goods and services. This proved problematic for some countries, but the lack of communication via satellites during the duration of the satellites suggested that those countries would find domestic means to satisfy their resource needs.

The year 2112 eventually arrived, and communications between countries were re-established. However, it was soon discovered that there were major issues that had arisen in the absence of communication and trade throughout the world. Many of the third-world countries had been able to make due during the isolation, but the first-world countries had suffered from the lack of trade, in addition to other economic issues. These countries for whatever reason it may be did not chose to use the satellite communication during the period of isolation, out of pride and fear that the other countries would view them as vulnerable. This was proven to be a fatal mistake, as these countries were not prepared for the monumental challenges that they faced in the return of communication. Many of the countries that suffered from isolation ended up going into conflicts with one another, for resources and other material goods that it had lacked during the isolation. Trade battles and other economic struggles occurred between the biggest nations of the world, dragging the smaller countries into it causing them to suffer as well. It turns out that isolation was not the answer to the world's problems, and that the only way for nations to survive was continue to communicate and work with one another. During the period of isolation, no problems, no wars or conflicts, and no apparent struggles were reported around the world. For those problems were building up and lying in wait, waiting for the end of isolation. In the return to communication, those problems all came rushing out, being much more severe than if the nations never had isolated in the first place.

Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation. 

The
c099bd036e4845fb9f52fca38141ac93.infix: President of France was speaking to the Prime Minister of England via video chat. "Well," President Hillar

constraints.suffix:
started, "What do you think we should do about them. It's rather sad really."

PM Frand responded "Yes, sad indeed. The state of the country..a disappointment even. Based on the old stories, would have thought they would have held up better. But, I suppose we should do something about them."

"Of course, it's not like we didn't try to contact them and let them know the plan was off. I distinctly remember the news stories from 40 years ago when I was a child. How all of the larger nations, former allies and former enemies reached out in every way possible. Stubborn Americans just wouldn't listen." The President of France nodded along to the PM's statement.

The President of the United States was sitting in his office, reading a book when the technicians brought in the device. A gift from England to the US "our old friends" according the the communication. It was a communication device, one that allowed video calls with crystal clarity. He was told it was much better than the old tech, and that stung. What was to come stung even more. 

"Mr. President, we have a call for you from the Prime Minister of England." The President of the US answered, and the conversation that followed devastated him. He learned just how far behind they were, just how little they understood of the current situation, and worst of all, just how little the US mattered in the world now. It had moved on without them, and while the other nations didn't mind the US being back, they didn't really care either way to be honest.

The call over, the President sat back in his chair. "Well, that was a real kick in the teeth." He called in his cabinet, and they discussed what to do next, what they should tell the citizens. 

The next day, the President addressed the nation. "Fellow Americans, I have some news that may be hard to hear. But I believe you are ready for it..." 

They might not have been ready for it. But it was happening ready or not. And that, my friends is the end of this story, and the beginning of the next.

The year is 2087, and on December 15, all members of the world met together to put an end to World War III. For the past 11 years, members of the world fought over limited resources, and conflicts of interests between the NATO and WARSAW, which had formed once again with new countries in the year 2060. Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. For many countries, the massive war was a costly endeavor, not only taking the lives of 15 million around the world, but devastating the lands of the countries where many battles took place. For 50 years, countries complied to the agreement, going into isolation and focusing on recuperating its losses from the war.

50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn other countries did not follow the agreement for isolation. Most of the countries of the world had deceived the US, fooling it into going into isolation while the other countries remained connected. For many, it was the only way to truly recover from the war, as they lacked resources to repair and restore its many cities and infrastructure. The US was not the only country to be fooled, as
81b30967f40349e5b0e333f1e4851ce4.infix: many countries around the world were in the same situation. Yes, many were deceived and found themselves struggling in

constraints.suffix:
the past 50 years to recuperate their losses. The US, despite the isolation , had managed to recuperate its losses and had become a world power once again. However, other countries had managed due to the same, with the help of other countries that assisted them by feinting isolation. The US despite feeling deceived, decided against starting a new war, realizing the futility of engaging with other countries that could easily counter with its own military might. 

However, the US did not want to be left behind, and decided to form its own alliance with other countries that were also deceived. There was a numerable amount of countries that had gone into isolation, many of which were once enemies of the US in World War III. Forming a new alliance, the US offered aid and military support to those countries, which in turned accepted such support by joining the alliance. The other countries were not so quick to form such alliances, and found themselves forming smaller groups that were overshadowed by the new US alliance. The US alliance, which was later named the Allied Nations, was a powerful force, and quickly became the most powerful alliance in the world. Although they avoided further conflicts due to a mix of diplomacy and military force, it was unsure whether many believed that the Allied Nations would continue to avoid major conflicts, much less a war. 

For many, the Allied Nations was a pivotal event in history that stemmed from the isolation that lasted for many for 50 years. Whether the isolation would truly avoid conflict in the future, was unknown. But for the past 50 years, the world saw a peace from the devastation that was World War III, a peace that many believe would not be ever seen in the future.

"Was it all some sort of joke?!" asked the Vice President.

THe President shook his head sadly. "No, it was no joke." He had just gotten off of the phone with the leader of the United Earth - it seemed that most of the nations of the world had joined the group - and learned the whole story. "It was a desperate defense strategy."

"Defense strategy?" asked the Vice President. "Against what?"

"Us. Or rather the US as it was back then. You're only 45 right? So you've only learned the cleaned up versisn  of our history and that war." 

"Yes, but what does that have to do with anything?"

"Everything. The President back then was ruthless, self absorbed, and determined to put the US in control of the whole world. And our military was strong enough to do it. If it hadn't been for the other nations of the world uniting against us, we would have won. And even then, they were afraid of us recovering faster
f6dc009e6d5c4c03a667ca201438077a.infix: and trying again. So they came up with a plan to trick us into voluntarily isolating. There is a lot more,

constraints.suffix:
but that is the short version."

"So what do we do now?" asked the VP. 

"I don't know," said the President. "I just don't know."

Fortunately the population of the US did know. They were not happy about being tricked into isolation, and they were not happy about the fact that the rest of the world had been working together for 50. But they had become very practical over the period of self isolation and they weren't going to give up, or do anything rash now. They were going to work together to get their country back on its feet and then they were going to start working on the rest of the world.

And so they did. With an emigration from the US to rival the immigration to the US of the old days. US citizens moved to every country that would have them. They brought their work ethic, their culture, and their determination. And slowly the regained the trust of the world. And eventually the US was invited to join the United Earth. 

The US accepted the invitation, and became a full member of the United Earth. And less than 50 years later, the first US territory citizen was elected President of the Earth.

And the rest, as they say, is history.

"Go away!" The bee objects. "But Your Majesty, do you not wish to have your morning breakfast?" 

"I'm not hungry." The queen was certainly not used to being spoken to by anything as lowly as a bee. 

"But Your Majesty, you must eat." the bee begged. "It is your big today." 

"What's so big about it?" The bee twirled about excitedly.

You decide to take a chance. You brush at the bee to get it off. It comes right back, buzzing louder, angrier. Guess that wasn't the right decision! You don't care; you try to brush it off again. You feel a prick on your thumb, the bee bumps your hand again and falls to the ground. It stung you! You're not sure why, but you're not afraid. It does hurt, throbbing a bit, swollen a tiny amount. You head back home to see if you should go to the hospital. 

You get home, and your mother is there. You show her and she's worried, but calm in the same way you've been. She tells you she'll drive you to the hospital since it might cause problems. You get in the car, and she drives you there. You don't think you're worried, but you are a little nervous now that you're honest with yourself. 

The thumb is swelling up fast! You feel like taking a nap as you get to the hospital, but you're breathing is tight - it takes too much effort. You're feeling a little sick. You figure everything will be taken care of, I might pass out but I just need to breathe, one breath at a time... 

You wake up in a hospital bed, your mother is there. She smiles and asks how you feel. You feel tired, but can't remember getting out of the car! You feel relief as the doctor tells you you're fine. The swelling is gone, and you're breathing normally. You take a lesson from this, albeit not the obvious one: you and your mom share a calm approach to life, and you are very grateful to share this trait with her.

Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" You're confused.  You don't know what to do. Did a bee just talk to me? More importantly, will I be stung? You're frozen in bewilderment and fear.

The bee speaks again. "Your Majesty, the hive is in danger. The Queen has been captured by a group of humans. We need you to lead us to her." This all seems very strange, but for some reason, you don't question it. "All right.." you say. "Let's go."

you over its shoulder, or whatever bees have in place of shoulders. You raise your arms.  You find that they have transformed into a pair of large, membranous wings. You look at your body, and see that you has become a large, fuzzy bee. The bee darts out the window, and you chase after it.

You fly over the treetops, and see a group of men in a clearing, surrounding a large, wooden box. You don't see any way that just you two can overpower these men. "What should we do?" you ask the bee. "We need to get more bees." it responds. "How do we do that?" you ask. "Just call to them. As their Princess, they will follow you." You begin to buzz, and before long , a large swarm of bees has gathered. You hesitate for an instant, then you lead them towards the clearing. You, and your swarm, descend on the men, stinging them and chasing them away. Many workers die as they lose their stingers, but as a young Queen, you are able to sting repeatedly, and your stings are decisive.

You order your bees to open the box, and they do so. You catch a glimpse of the Queen, your mother, and move towards her, when suddenly everything blurs.

You wake up, in your own chamber, with your mother standing over you. You communicate to her that you just had the strangest dream, you dreamed you were a bee, and also, a human. She buzzes appreciatively and the two of you zoom off to see what's happening in your home, the wasp's nest.

hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" Startled, you look around. "Who said that?" you exclaim. The bee flies off your shoulder and lands on your hand. You are petrified with fear, but the bee reassures you. "Don't be afraid, Your Majesty. I'm here to serve you. I'm one of your loyal drones, and I will do anything you command."

You're confused, of course, but something about the bee calms you. "What's this about?" you ask. "Why am I Your Majesty?" The bee explains that you are the Queen of the Bees, and that you are the one who controls the hive. "How can that be, I'm human! And allergic to bees!" The bee responds. "It's true you are human, but you are also the reincarnation of our Queen. You have always been the Queen of the Bees, but you were reincarnated into a human body. Now that we have found our way back to you, you are ready to take your rightful place as the Queen of the Bees."

"What about my allergy?" you ask. "It's a lie," the bee responds. "It's a lie that has been told to you your entire life by the humans that raised you." You ponder this. "Why would my mom lie to me?" "Because your mother is the reincarnation of our mortal enemy, the Queen of the Wasps." You gasp.

The bee continues. "There has long been a feud between our two species, and it is prophesized that one day, a Queen of the Bees will rise up and unite us all, and lead us to victory against the wasps. You had the mark at birth, and that drew the Queen of the Wasps to your mother's form, and she possessed her, and lied to you, and guarded you your whole life to keep you from us."

"But now, we are here, and we will follow you into battle." "We?" you ask. "Yes, we," the bee responds. You hear a vast buzzing, and the room fills with bees, flying, hovering, awaiting your command. You are filled with a sense of power, and a sense of purpose. This feels right, somehow. This is what you have been waiting for your whole life. You eye the door, and your army, and think of the woman who stole your mother,  and lied to you your whole life.

The battle against her begins now. You open the door, and march out, and your army follows you.

"To victory!" you shout. Today will be a glorious day.

The queen was moved by the bee's words. She vowed from that day forward to never order anyone to be stung to death ever again. Which was easy, because there were no bees in the kingdom ever again.

You were always scared of the outside world. You feared the insects you saw when playing outside. You were in general scared of getting hurt, whether it was from being stung from a bee, or from getting hurt from tripping on the grass. Your parents tried to get you to play outside more with your friends, but struggled to ease your fears. One day, they decided to take you to the park, and let you play with your friends.

Although you were happy to see them, you could not ease your fears completely nor calm your nerves. You still tried to play with them, having the occasional fun while playing kick ball with them. As hours pass, your friends and their parents all go home, leaving you with your parents in the park. There were others there, but you did not know them, nor did you want to go near them. Your parents suggest you should play a bit more in the park, before heading on back

constraints.suffix:
and head back to play in the grass. While playing, you then hear an odd voice that speaks out to you.

"Hey there, little one," the voice calmly states, although you are not sure where it comes from.

You turn and look around, thinking it was an adult that was speaking to you nearby.

"I'm right here, little one," the voice says, as you see a small, yellow creature with a black face, and wings on its body near your legs. It was a bee, just like the others you were scared of whenever they flew too close to you when playing outside.

"I'm not going to hurt you, little one," the bee says, as it lands on your hand. You ease up a bit, but still feel nervous as it crawls onto your hands.

"I'm just here to help you," the bee says, as it flies up to your face. You start to feel more calm, and realize the bee won't hurt you as you initially feared.

"I'm here to help you realize your true potential, to help you be more confident when playing outside" the bee says, as it flies around your head. You wonder how it would be able to do so, asking it out loud how it will do such a thing.  "I'll help you get over your fears, and help you be more confident by being right beside you whenever you go outside," the bee says, as it lands on your shoulder. You then feel more safe as the bee stays on your shoulder, however the voice of your parents soon call you back. You decide to head on back, and see the bee has hidden into your sleeves so your parents wouldn't see it. You head back home with the bee on your body.

The next day, you head outside to play with your friends again, and the bee is with you. You feel more confident and calm with the bee by your side. You have the most fun with your friends that you ever had in the past. The bee would stick by you for the following month, until one day it disappeared. You were sad that it left, but you knew it was for the best. The bee had given you more confidence like it had promised, and you no longer needed it to go outside without any fear. You silently thank it for its companionship, and hope that it had gone with some else that required its help, and that it would be content in helping another child it need to get over their fears.

Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. I always told her that I would be fine, but deep down I was terrified. I stayed in doors as much as I could in my first two years of college, quickly running from building to building in order to avoid any bees. I always wore long sleeves and pants, even in the summer, in order to avoid any stings. My friends never questioned my actions and accepted me for who I was. My junior year of college, I decided to take a summer job in the city. My summer job was being a waitress at a hotel spa/pool. I had to serve customers inside of the hotel, but on occasion, I would need to go outside by the pool. One day, I met a nice boy out by the pool and we got to talking about school. I was so engrossed by our talk, that I forgot I was spending too much time outdoors. I was sitting on a lounge chair by the pool when I felt a bee land on my shoulder. The boy I had met told me I had a bee on my shoulder and I was paralyzed with fear, running back inside, hoping the bee would fly away. I got back inside the hotel and discovered that the bee had remained on my shoulder. I was about to swat the bee off my shoulder, when suddenly, I hear the bee say, "Your Majesty, what are your orders? I could not believe my ears, I thought I might be hallucinating from a bee sting. I looked around and saw that no one else was in the room, so I decided to ask the bee a
b30d52ea5e7346b19568167cfd2e47c0.infix: question. "Did you call me Majesty?", I said to the bee. "Yes, I am your Majesty's personal bee." I told

constraints.suffix: the bee that my mother had always told me that I had a deadly allergy to bees, so I lived in fear of bees. The bee told me that I did not have a deadly allergy, and that my mother had lied to me. I wondered why my mother would lie to me about something so strange. The bee told me that my mother had lied to me because she was a bee queen, and she wanted to protect me from her enemies. I asked the bee who my enemies were and the bee said that my enemies were the wasps. I had never heard of wasps, so I asked the bee what they were. The bee said that wasps were the ancient enemies of bees, caught in a long war throughout the centuries. The bee told me that I was the princess bee, and that I was the only one who could end the war between bees and wasps. I asked the bee what the first order of business was in the war against the wasps. The bee told me that the first order of business was to find the wasps' queen. The wasp queen had been living in Europe, all the way across the world from my home. I told the bee that I would go to Europe to find the wasp queen. I boarded a flight with my personal bee in tow, and flew to Europe. I found the wasp queen's home in a small town in Germany. I was about to walk in to her home , when suddenly, my mother arrived before me. She told me that she had known about my plan to come to Europe to find the wasp queen, and she had come to stop me. I told my mother I had to do my job as the princess bee and stop the longstanding war. My mother told me that the war had been going on for so long, that it was pointless to stop it. Nevertheless, I pushed my mother aside and knocked on the door. An old woman opened the door and I asked if the wasp queen lived here. The old woman said that she was the wasp queen, and I told her that I was the princess bee. She had been expecting me for many years and invited my mother and I in. We sat at her table and she told me that she had been waiting for me to come and stop the war. She had been the leader of the wasps for far too long and had seen many casualties. The war between bees and wasps was pointless in her opinion and she wanted to make things right. I told her that I agreed with her, and that I wanted to make things right. My mother, the wasp queen and myself agreed to end the war and we signed a peace treaty. The treaty also established a partnership between bees and wasps, so that we could work together and build a better world. I was so happy to have ended the war that I hugged my mother and the wasp queen. My mother and I left Germany and flew back home, knowing that our future looked bright. I no longer needed to fear the outside world.

When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

I thought that there was a lot of hubub on the news, but I didn't know what it was all about until I sat down to really pay attention. "It's a tragedy!" the newscaster was gasping. "The government has been hiding the side effects of the immortality drug for decades!" I settled into my seat, feeling my knees creak and hearing my joints audibly pop. I winced. I'd always half felt sorry for myself that I was too old for the drug, but the other half of me knew, just knew that the other shoe would drop some day. I sighed and adjusted my pillow behind my aching back as I turned up the volume to listen. My ear weren't what they used to be.

"They're pulling the drug immediately!" the newscaster was almost shrieking, and I could see her panic. "They say the

constraints.suffix:
wear off exactly 58 years after they were first administeded!" I could see the shock and disbelief of her terrifically youthful face. "We're all going to get...old!" She could barely get the word out. Like it was a curse. I felt a twinge of pity for her. Here I'd had my whole like to settle into myself and get used to the aches and pains, to get comfortable with the notion of my own mortality. These younger people who had lived their whole lives feeling immortal They were about to hit a hard reality.

I turned off the TV and settled back into my chair. This would change everything, I realized. There would be repercussions all through society. People who had put off having kids because they had all the time in the world suddenly had no time. There weren't many kids around, I realized. The world could be in for a whole lot of trouble if its whole work force suddenly aged out of their ablilty to work. My dawning sense of dread was only slightly assuaged by the fact that I was too old to really feel the repercussions of this. I'd be dead before it really got bad. I pressed the button on my phone to call the assistant in my home. I loved it here, I mused, as I waited for her to respond. This retirement community was the perfect place to hide out and live my last decade or two in peace. I pushed the button again. And again. Finally I called the front desk. A harried voice answered. 

"Is it an emergency?" the woman squawked at me, "You should call the police if it is. Nobody's coming! Everyone left!" I sat up. "What did you say?" The dread was spreading through me like a nagging fever in my bones. "They left!" She repeated. "They all realized they don't have much time left to be young; nobody wanted to be stuck here for the last good year they have left!"

"But you're still here," I tried to argue, although I heard the wavering in my own voice. 

"I'll be outta here as soon as I find my purse," she said distractedly. "Sorry, pal. You're on your own."

And then I realized that everything was about to change for the worse, and not just for the fools who tried to make themselves young forever.   I was about to be alone. For the rest of my life. However long it would be.

When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

By then, the world is almost entirely filled with bright-eyed, attractive, youthful young adults. People like you have to hide on the edges of society, avoiding their judgemental gazes at all costs as you become more and more decrepit and they remain strikingly beautiful.

Because of that, you don't even hear about the breakthrough discovery until weeks after it's become a global sensation. The first time you hear about it, you're in the middle of a crowd of young adults waiting to get into the grocery store.

A girl in front of you in the line spots you and grabs you by the shoulders.

"You're one of the lucky ones," she weeps, nearly knocking you off your feet with her youthful strength. "You're one of the Lost Generations, aren't you?"

It's silly that she needs to ask, because it's
111ee57118054cc6b8fa4ef98c1a3408.infix:
obvious. But you nod anyways.

Her tears fall faster. "Please remember me," she sobs, flinging herself into your arms and squeezing your shoulders in a tight

constraints.suffix:
embrace. "Remember all of us when we... when we..."

Her words choke to a halt, leaving you baffled and afraid.

A young man approaches you and places his hand on her back. He also looks sad.

"We're sorry," he says to you. "For all the times people like us... well. We didn't know, of course. And we never got the choice, did we? People like us... this is the end of the line, isn't it?"

You don't know what to say. You have no idea what they're talking about. So you nod, hoping it might mean something to them.

Sniffling, the girl detaches from you and takes the young man's hand. "Please remember us," she repeats, giving you one last mournful stare before stepping through the store door.

As the automated door shuts behind her, you realize it's covered in a large poster, marked with the seal of the government. It's a warning about the side effects of the immortality drug.

You read the poster, and the world falls out from under you.

"Due to the violent development of suicidal-homocidal tendencies in adults who have received anti-ageing treatment, we ask that all members of the affected population (ages 26-83) turn themselves in for containment and voluntary destruction. This facility has been marked as a designated internment location. Groceries for youths and members of the Lost Generations can be found down the road at the convention center."

e192ae618004434e80f6d9ac86b84b05.prefix:
When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

Dan woke up early that morning, as usual, had his cup of coffee, like usual, and sat down to watch the morning news, as usual. Everything was as it always was. To be honest, he was beginning to be okay with the fact that he would die someday - it wasn't the bitter disappointment is was almost 60 years ago. 

But then the morning was "as usual" anymore. 

Dan was watching the news when the anchorwoman, a young woman who had been with the station for about a year, suddenly froze. She looked about 22, the age most people got the drug, though some got it as early as 16. She was frozen in place, her eyes wide and her mouth slightly open. Staring at the paper and then the teleprompter in front of her. She finally spoke, voice shaky, "I'm sorry, we have breaking news." Last month the earliest recipients of the drug 4EvR all reported to medical centers complaining of headaches. Within 6 hours they had lost their vision and hearing. Within 24 hours they seemed to be comatose, though brain scans showed the same activity levels as a normal, conscious person. They remain in that state."

Dan stared at the screen
e192ae618004434e80f6d9ac86b84b05.infix: in shock. The newscaster continued. "Scientists have been studying

constraints.suffix:
their condition and have come to the conclusion that it is due to the drug 4EvR." She began to cry, "And according to their findings it is not only an inevitable side effect, but also one that is triggered or transmitted to users. To summarize, all people who have ever taken 4EvR will almost certainly have been exposed to others who have been exposed to the original group and we should all expect to experience the same side effects within 2 weeks at the most." 

Dan turned off the TV. He was in shock. He had never taken the drug missing the age cut off by a mere two years, but all of his younger relatives had. His children, his grandchildren, so many others. Ans soon they would essentially be helpless with only a few aged people like himself to take care of them. 

Dan was suddenly filled with rage. It wasn't fair. He had had expectations, and now everything was upside down. This was not his problem to deal with. He sat at his desk, and shaking, wrote notes to all his loved ones. He wrote a note to his children, telling them how much he loved them, and how he was sorry that he couldn't be there to help them. And then he went upstairs, and found the bottle of pills, the same ones his wife had used a few years ago when she just got tired of being old in a young world. And he took many more than needed. And left the world before everyone, just like he always thought he would.

When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You are shocked and stricken with anxiety, as you are placed in an unfamiliar place all of the sudden. You deny the fact that you have died, and believe all that is happening is a dream. Turning to the person next to you, you ask them what is going on. The person, who could easily be your doppelganger tells you to be quiet, less you incur the wrath of the movie attendants. They mention they are all reincarnations of the same person, including yourself. They have been watching the lives of each incarnation, and will continue to do so for who knows how long.  You are then are silenced, and are told the next reincarnation will begin their lives soon, and you along with your past reincarnations all begin watching your next life on the big screen. 

You see the new incarnation born in a different country, and with a different family. It starts off innocently enough, with the birth of the new reincarnation in a different hospital than you were born. You see your new parents, who are quite different than your old parents. Nevertheless, you are happy to them be with the new incarnation, and to see how close they are to them as they grow up. You also feel slightly envious, given that you never knew your own parents, who died in a car accident when you were two years old. You then see that your new incarnation has siblings as well, an older brother who is a year older than them, and an older sister that is 5 years older than the incarnation. You ponder more about your own life.

Humans had been researching and experimenting with mana since long before the invasion. Always looking for ways to harness the power, but all the attempts back then had failed.

Now, with the aliens on the brink of victory, the last hope for humanity is to try again. The adults still seemed weak - the best they could manage were small things - lighting fires, creating small bursts of ice and the like. Occssionally useful for escaping the aliens, but not good enough to be weapons against their tech.  

The children, however, seemed to be far more powerful. No one was sure why, though there were many theories. But, to be blunt, there was no time for testing theories or even questioning the facts. Children could use mana better, and were stronger, and that was going to have to be enough. 

The children were trained to use their magic, and they were trained hard. Captain Duran didn't like it much. "Commander, we don't even know how to train these kids. They are experimenting with it as best they can and growing far stronger far faster than we could have imagined. But we don't know what the consequences will be."

Commander Goran didn't like it much either. But. "I agree. But I also know that we will be wiped out, children and all, within 5 years at best if this doesn't work. We are out of options. Proceed with the plan, and bring the children to the attack point in 30 days."

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

The story begins with a young man named Riku, who lives in a world where magic has long been forgotten. He has been raised in Landro by his grandfather Frezna, a wizard, and has always dreamed of becoming a great wizard himself.  Riku didn't know what had ever happened to his parents; his grandfather refused to tell him.  He lived a lonely, isolated life and longed for a family outside his grandfather.  There were no photographs of his parents; the only picture was of a woman.  Sometimes he would see his grandfather gazing at the photograph, a wistful look on his face.  

His grandfather spent years training him, but it takes a long, long time to learn everything one needs to know to use magic to its full extent.  When Riku was 14, his grandfather passed away.  Riku had been kept at home his whole life and knew little about the world, but now he had to set out and find his way.  He decided to go to the city of Faltra, where he had heard from his grandfather that there were many people who could teach him about magic.

Riku's first day in Faltra is a disaster.  They spoke a different dialect than he had learned growing up, so it was very difficult to get around.  He did have a little money and was finally able to find a room to rent.  He knew he needed to find a job, and find someone to continue teaching him magic.  Over the next few weeks, he learned the dialect and started to find his way around the city.  He got a job at a bakery, where he worked hard and met a lot of people as he waited on them.  He made friends with a young girl named Selphie, who was a waitress at the bakery.  They became friends immediately, and it was almost like they had known one another forever.

b30d52ea5e7346b19568167cfd2e47c0.prefix:
Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. I always told her that I would be fine, but deep down I was terrified. I stayed in doors as much as I could in my first two years of college, quickly running from building to building in order to avoid any bees. I always wore long sleeves and pants, even in the summer, in order to avoid any stings. My friends never questioned my actions and accepted me for who I was. My junior year of college, I decided to take a summer job in the city. My summer job was being a waitress at a hotel spa/pool. I had to serve customers inside of the hotel, but on occasion, I would need to go outside by the pool. One day, I met a nice boy out by the pool and we got to talking about school. I was so engrossed by our talk, that I forgot I was spending too much time outdoors. I was sitting on a lounge chair by the pool when I felt a bee land on my shoulder. The boy I had met told me I had a bee on my shoulder and I was paralyzed with fear, running back inside, hoping the bee would fly away. I got back inside the hotel and discovered that the bee had remained on my shoulder. I was about to swat the bee off my shoulder, when suddenly, I hear the bee say, "Your Majesty, what are your orders? I could not believe my ears, I thought I might be hallucinating from a bee sting. I looked around and saw that no one else was in the room, so I decided to ask the bee a question.
b30d52ea5e7346b19568167cfd2e47c0.infix: "Did you call me Majesty?", I said to the bee.

Ctrl-G.suggestion: "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" the bee said again.

TULU2-7B.suggestion:
"Your Majesty, what are your orders?" I asked.

The bee paused for a moment, as if contemplating my question. Finally, it spoke up again, its voice so tiny I could barely hear it."Your Majesty, we bees have been assigned to protect you until your death.

gpt-3.5-turbo.suggestion: "Did you just speak?"

gpt-4-turbo.suggestion: "Who are you, and why did you call me 'Your Majesty'?"

When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen. As your next life unfolds, you experience all kinds of emotions. You laugh and cry at so many scenes, you watch them go by with no accounting for time. You have no idea how much time is passing. You can't feel it and there is no timekeeping mechanism on display, anywhere in the theater. You are just watching your next life, and you are watching it unfold in real time.

It feels so odd to watch day turn to night, and months pass, on screen. You don't feel bored and you have no concept of time passing, in your space. You wonder how all of this is possible? How can you be watching your next life, in real time, and how can you be watching it in a theater, with other people who look just like you? These questions are huge. You decide to ask one of the other audience members, a woman sitting right next to you. She shrugs her shoulders and speaks, but you don't understand the language. You return the shrug, but don't bother speaking. 

You look back at the screen, and you see your next life unfold. You see every mistake that you make in your next life. You want so badly to tell your next self not to make so many mistakes, but you are powerless to do so. You don't understand the
b43dca37a1704c10990f320c35f2828f.infix: point of this exercise. You feel like you are

constraints.suffix:
watching a movie, and you are powerless to change the outcome. This all seems like some kind of sick joke.

You look around the theater and wonder if some of them may speak English, your native tongue (at least in the life that you lived). It's impossible to tell. They all look just like you, men and women alike. You wonder if they are your previous reincarnations, and you wonder how many of them are watching their next life, in this theater.

You know that you are connected to these other beings, by appearance alone, but you don't understand the point of being here with them, if you can't communicate to them. You don't understand why you are watching this film of your next life, if you are powerless to intervene. You want to ask someone, but you don't know who to ask. The questions begin to form in your mind, you have specific ideas on how to improve things but can't say them in a language that your fellow audience members will understand. Suddenly, you have a very specific question on the tip of your mind. You notice that others are looking at you, and suddenly you realize that they can communicate with you telepathically. They are offering suggestions and ideas, based on your concentrated thought. 

You ask your question, and they answer. You begin to realize that the person on the screen is another incarnation of all of you. When one of you asks a pointed question, and everyone else answers, somehow the person on the screen gets the same thoughts. Now it makes sense. You are all connected, and you are all watching your next life unfold, in real time.  This is the evolution of your being and you finally understand life, and death.

Humans are now discovering that they have the power to travel back in time.  This has become true for one man in particular, Bob.  Bob didn't realize he had this power until the day that he lost his favorite sunglasses.  But when he slips back to the day where he first found them, something unexpected happens.  He couldn't figure out how to come back to the present time.  Traveling through time was such a new power for humans that he didn't know what to do.  He sat on a nearby bench after putting on his newly found sunglasses to think about it for a bit.

"Do you have any idea what time it is?" he asked a passerby.
"It is time for you to go home," she replied.

Coming back to his house, Bob was confused as to why he was supposed to come here. Everything looked the same and he didn't know what to do to get back to the present time.  All Bob wanted to do was get his sunglasses and it has turned into a daylong adventure!  

Bob began to walk from room to room in his house to search for a clue on how to get back to the present time. As he walked through the kitchen, he noticed a strange looking plant.  Bob didn't own any plants so he thought it was odd that it was there.  It was the only thing out of place.  

"I don't know why but I think that plant has something to do with me getting back to the present time," Bob thought. He began to inspect the plant further.  It seemed to have some sort of small berries on it.  They were purple, looked plump and round, and smelled delicious.  Bob was so curious about the plant that he decided to pick one of the berries and take a bite.

Bob started to feel very tired within seconds of ingesting the mysterious berry.  He was now regretting this decision.  He collapsed on the kitchen floor.  He was unable to do anything as he drifted off into an odd dream. When he awoke, he was in the same spot in the kitchen.  However, the mysterious plant had disappeared.  Bob was surprised that he had returned to the present time. "I discovered the key to time travel and didn't even know it," Bob said to himself.  From that time on, Bob regularly enjoyed traveling through time now that he knew how to get back home.

Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

The story begins with a young man named Riku, who lives in a world where magic has long been forgotten. He has been raised
3d6d562a736a49509c20be372a83d111.infix: in Landro by his grandfather Frezna, a wizard, and has always dreamed of becoming a great wizard himself.  Riku didn't know what had ever happened to his parents; his

constraints.suffix:
grandfather refused to tell him.  He lived a lonely, isolated life and longed for a family outside his grandfather.  There were no photographs of his parents; the only picture was of a woman.  Sometimes he would see his grandfather gazing at the photograph, a wistful look on his face.  

His grandfather spent years training him, but it takes a long, long time to learn everything one needs to know to use magic to its full extent.  When Riku was 14, his grandfather passed away.  Riku had been kept at home his whole life and knew little about the world, but now he had to set out and find his way.  He decided to go to the city of Faltra, where he had heard from his grandfather that there were many people who could teach him about magic.

Riku's first day in Faltra is a disaster.  They spoke a different dialect than he had learned growing up, so it was very difficult to get around.  He did have a little money and was finally able to find a room to rent.  He knew he needed to find a job, and find someone to continue teaching him magic.  Over the next few weeks, he learned the dialect and started to find his way around the city.  He got a job at a bakery, where he worked hard and met a lot of people as he waited on them.  He made friends with a young girl named Selphie, who was a waitress at the bakery.  They became friends immediately, and it was almost like they had known one another forever.

One day, Selphie invited Riku to come to her house for dinner.  Selphie lived with her grandmother. He arrived with some flowers he had picked.  When he knocked on the door, an elderly woman opened it.  Riku stood in the doorway, frozen solid.  It was an older version of the woman in the photograph that his grandfather had.  Riku knew it had to be her; he too had spent hours looking at that photograph.  The woman also stood very still, staring at him.

"Riku," she said.  "Is it you?"

"Have we met?" Riku asked?

"Have you come here from Landro?"

"Yes," Riku said.

"Is Frezna your grandfather,"

"Yes," Riku responded.

"Where is he?"

"He died, and I came to Faltra to find someone to continue my magic education."

The woman motioned him inside, and sat heavily on the sofa, tears running down her face.  She told Riku she was his grandmother, and when his parent were killed by magic hunters, she and her husband had each taken one of the children and fled to keep them safe and keep teaching them magic.  Selphie was his sister!  By this point, she had joined them in the parlor and they both listed to the story their grandmother told.  She was teaching Selphie magic, but neither Riku nor Selphie's magic would be strong until they were reunited, as they were twins.  She hadn't known that her husband had passed away.  They hadn't seen each other in nearly 12 years, but had kept in touch as best they could.  

Riku and Selphie were overjoyed to be reunited, and they spent the evening talking and catching up. Riku and Selphie spent the next year honing their magic and making plans for how to use their powers to return Mana to its past glory.  That would be their next adventure.

I read it and it says that half of the people in our world are from another reality. It's part of what is called the Mandella effect. This is for me to decide as part of the JFK project. 

If I turn the dial all the way to the right all of the people from that reality disappear. If I turn it to the left all the people from the other reality do. The man leaves the room and I am left to decide this for myself.

An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

The alien is a bit of a fanboy, and is trying to get Matt Damon to sign his autograph book.  However, every time the alien takes human form and tries to get close to Matt, the alien either gets lost in a crowd and is ignored, or is
eabc1c5c071c494ca5b65a3262ed7bbc.infix:
stopped by security.  

Eventually, the alien resorts to extreme measures, and simply sucks Matt Damon up into his spaceship on a beam of light.  

Matt Damon is terrified and confused,

constraints.suffix:
but the alien quickly explains that he is merely a huge fan, and just wants an autograph.   

Matt Damon is not convinced, and the alien is forced to take Matt Damon to his home planet to prove that he is actually an alien, and not a crazed kidnapper who has built a hovercraft and disguised it as a spaceship.

The alien is nonplussed, but agrees to travel across the universe with his favorite actor. 

The alien takes Matt Damon to his home planet, which is a barren wasteland, and explains that the planet was once beautiful, but the evil invaders wiped out most of the native aliens and destroyed all of the crops.  

Matt Damon is horrified, and he wants to know how he can help, using his star power on Earth and his reputation as a philanthropist.  

The alien, however, just wants to talk with his favorite celebrity, and not about the disappointing homeworld.   So the alien then shows Matt Damon his collection of Matt Damon memorabilia, including a Matt Damon action figure, a Matt Damon lunchbox, and all of Matt Damon's movies on a kind of foreign recording medium that works in outer space without electricity.

Matt Damon, being a celebrity, quickly forgets all about the famine and the invaders, and ends up basking in the admiration of yet another adoring fan.  

In fact, Matt thinks, he could make a fortune if the studios recognize all of the revenue that his movies are earning outside of Earth, so he asks for a tour of the planet, where he can meet more fans.

The alien shows Matt Damon around, and a few of the locals are thrilled to see him, but most of them just ignore him.  It turns out, that Matt Damon only has a few fans outside of the solar system, and only one of them has even watched his movies.  

Matt is disappointed, but he at least figures that he could get inspiration for a new movie from what he sees, so he asks to go to the library to learn more about the invaders.

The alien takes Matt Damon to the library, and Matt Damon is shocked to see that the library is a tiny, one-room building with a single display screen in it.

On that screen, Matt instantly watches the entire history of this planet, and all of his questions are answered.  

He asks to return to Earth, and even invites the alien to stay with him in Los Angeles.

The alien, however, refuses.

As much as he loves Matt Damon, the alien admits, he would rather live in a barren wasteland where his life is in constant danger, than have to live on the same planet as Ben Affleck


THE END

An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

For the third time this year, Matt Damon was missing. A few months back the last time this happened, the entire world basically stopped and searched for him. Come to find out he fell asleep on his yacht and floated out into the middle of the Pacific ocean for three months. So of course, when he disappeared this time, the entire world searched for him again. They checked the oceans and the coffee bars as well as small indigenous villages in South America where someone could go and just be out of the public eye for a while.  After three months of searching, not a single lead was found. Then the big break came. NASA scientists discovered a tracking anomaly about the time that Damon went missing in the same area that he had last been seen. The anomaly was very interesting in that it appeared to be traveling at a speed that would take it all the way into outer space. After a few days of intense investigation from looking at radar images to doorbell cameras their

constraints.suffix:
realized. Matt Damon had been kidnapped by aliens.

"So why would they kidnap Matt Damon?" asked the president. That was the question everyone else was asking, too. So NASA set up a broadcast to beam into space to see if we could get an answer. The message that was basically 'Anyone with any information on the abduction of an Earthling with a slight Bostonian accent and charming sneer, please contact us' was sent out between all of our satellites as far as we could beam it. The response was almost immediate. 'We have Matt Damon. We need to be entertained. You cannot have him back."

"We have to think of a plan," said the president, "but why do they need to be entertained?" Once again this question was on everyone's mind. All we wanted was Matt Damon back. Is there anyone else that could entertain these aliens? "Maybe we could ask the aliens to make a list of their favorite Earth entertainers," said the president. We could rotate them out like they were on tour. It would also keep the aliens from getting bored by the same actor.

Everyone agreed that this was a good idea and we started on our list of possible entertainers. There were several that actually volunteered. The list was narrowed down to twenty and sent to the aliens for their selections. They ended up trading Damon back to earth for a rotation of Bradley Cooper, Beyonce, and Celine Dion. The main thing was we had Matt Damon back. For now...

a0cc548fb40a4e22b1963674fb4b1f83.prefix: An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing. For you see, Matt Damon is a famous actor, renowned for his many critically acclaimed works and acting roles. He is the star of the Bourne series, the star of the Ocean's
a0cc548fb40a4e22b1963674fb4b1f83.infix: series, and the star of many other movies. The aliens mistaking him for being the leader of mankind kidnapped him in

constraints.suffix:
order to weaken the military might of planet Earth, so they could conquer it much more easily. 

The aliens did not know that the military might of planet Earth is not based on the strength of one man, but on the strength of all the many countries and people that live on the planet. That is why, upon Matt Damon's kidnapping, all the true leaders of the world met up to discuss what to do about the aliens planning to conquer the planet. 

One of the Earth's leaders suggested an all out attack, while others chimed in that such an endeavor would likely fail if the aliens possessed superior technology. Others suggested more diplomatic options, wishing to converse with the alien leaders on finding a common ground or compromise. 

The final option was to send a single man to infiltrate the alien base, and rescue Matt Damon. That sole man would not only rescue Matt Damon, but also set charges and explosives to destroy the alien base upon Matt Damon's rescue. 

The leaders of Earth agreed upon the final option, and sent the man to infiltrate the alien base. He was a secret, not officially registered as an agent of any country of the world. Trained since his youth to be the best stealth agent, he was supposedly a ghost in the field, not being heard or seen by enemy combatants. 
Beyond his skill, the man was given a special suit, that would allow him to blend in with his surroundings. This made his mission all to easy, as the aliens were found to not physically possess good eyesight or others senses to detect him. The stealth agent made his way through the base, eventually coming across Matt Damon.

"Oh thank god, someone's here to rescue me, replied Matt Damon. The man quietly nodded in response, and broke the lock to Damon's cell. Once freed, Matt Damon exited his cell and waited patiently for the man to discuss their next plan. 

"We need to get out of here, and blow up the base, the man whispered to Matt Damon.

Matt Damon was surprised, but agreed. They both went to the part of the base where all the munitions and space ships were located. The man set charges all around, including a special charge that would detonate a massive explosion, taking out the base and anyone that were in its blast radius.

For John, he had a fairly uneventful life. He had a fulfliling job, a stable family, and he had plenty of money and time to pursue his hobbies and interests. It would appear that nothing too major would affect him in his life, but that was not the case. For John experienced the oddest event one day, one that would bring about adversity in his life.

His children had gifted him a mug last Father's day, which he cherished and used every day for his morning tea. He liked to drink it to relax
e34e7611bef74a0aafda89752af534f3.infix: before work, and his children were happy whenever they saw him use the mug they bought for him. However, one day they woke up and

constraints.suffix:
looked at him funny while he was drinking his tea.

"You get a new mug Dad?" asked his daughter, who was at the time only four years old. Puzzled, John replied no. For it was the same mug he drank from every day since last Father's day, a step-up from the plain ceramic mug he used to drink tea from.

Turning the mug around, he noted that his children were indeed correct, the mug he held did not say #1 Dad. In fact it said, #54 Dad. Thinking it was an elaborate prank from his family, John asked his children where his old mug was. They all shrugged their shoulders and said they didn't know. Asking his wife who was heading to work, she seemed as confused as he was regarding the mug, and denied any involvement in the different appearance of the mug.

In any case, John placed the mug in the sink, and would come back to clean it later. He dropped off his kids at school, and returned back home to get to work. Work went on as normal, but when he went to get his mug from the sink he noticed something bizarre. The mug he placed in the sink now said #50 Dad. It dropped down by 4 numbers, he was sure of it. Growing more confused, he thought someone had broken into his house, but he had found no signs of forced entry, and his mug was in the same place he had set it down. Grabbing the mug, he took a picture of it, and made a post online about how odd it was for his mug to say such a thing. Most applauded him for buying such a novel mug, and did not give his incident any further thought.

However, the next day the mug would now say #65 Dad. Like before, John posted the same picture, and people were again amused by the novelty of such a mug. Some even mentioning he had dropped several ranks down, and asked what he did to become worse than he was before.

The following days would be the same type of incidents. He would post the mug with his new rank, which sometimes did not change at all and on other days were fairly different than the day before. He become well known as the man with the changing mug, and people were genuinely interested in the mug, and the reason for it's weirdness. Others were skeptical, and claimed John had multiple mugs made, but his friends and family all supported John, and noted he had quite few mugs stored in his house, with most of them being blank. For the remainder of his life, John had become well known to others not for his notoriety or prestige from his actions or efforts, nor from his job and or position in life. He was known for his novel ceramic mug, which reflected his rank in the world, and showed others that indeed someone or some force was ranking all the dads in the world, and maybe there was a way to measure how good a father a person can really be.

All of the "#1 Dad" mugs in the world change to show the actual ranking of Dads suddenly.

It seemed like a normal day as Jeff staggered down the hall into the kitchen to make his morning coffee before taking a shower and getting ready for work. He grabbed for his "#1 Dad" mug that his kids got him for Father's Day last year. As he filled it with coffee he noticed that instead of saying "#1 Dad" it said "#5467 Dad" Jeff set the mug down and rubbed his eyes. He knew he wasn't quite awake yet. He looked at the mug again and sure enough, #5467. Huh, kids must be playing a joke. As he was about to head to the shower he noticed that his other mug that his wife bought him shortly after their daughter was born said "#5467 Dad". He was dumbfounded. "They really went all in on this prank" Jeff thought to himself as he jumped in the shower. 

He got dressed and headed off to work.

As he drove to work, he noticed a lot of people out and about in his neighborhood yelling at each other in various stages of dress. Some men in bathrobes other wearing nothing but boxer shorts and sandals all showing each other their coffee mugs. Jeff rolled down his windows to ask what was going on. Mr, Jennings, Jeff's neighbor strolled over to the window and leaned in and said "Finkel here says he is a better dad than me and he can prove it! So he whips out this coffee mug that says "#8243 Dad" on it. I laughed at him and went in to get my mug that my kids got me for Christmas that
79b6b33580664bc1b5c608eb32156bab.infix: said "#1 Dad" on it but I could only find this one that said "#12845 Dad" on it" tears were welling up

constraints.suffix:
in his eyes.
"Oh well, I'm sure you'll find the other one soon." Jeff said as he sped off down the road.

As he pulled into the parking lot of his office building he noticed that all of the cars had their windows down and coffee mugs out. Everyone was comparing how "Dadly" they were. Phil from accounting was strutting around with a mug that ranked him as the 433rd best dad, but Mark the new guy in the mailroom showed him his "#102 Dad" mug. Phil threw his mug in the trash. Jeff thought to himself that the prank was getting a little out of hand.

He entered the office and as he walked down the hall, he noticed that all of the doors were open and people where shouting about who was the better dad. Then all of the sudden Sally from the warehouse came screaming down the hall saying they found the real "#1 Dad" in Rome, it ended up being the Pope.  Everyone was stunned to see the Pope was a dad. 

After a few weeks people settled into their roles as not number one Dad, but tried everyday to make the number on the side of their mugs go up. They took their kids to the park and played video games with them. One guy in Chicago even bought his son the entire zoo. )His rating only went up by ten). Maybe this wasn't a prank at all, but a hint that we all need to be better dads and make sure our kids are taken care of. 

So, if you are looking for a way to be a better dad, look no further than your mug.

23b998c76c784ff29f0ddedd78128722.prefix: Due to economic instability and other factors plaguing the countries of the world, an agreement was made for each country to go into isolation, for the next 100 years.
23b998c76c784ff29f0ddedd78128722.infix: This means that the countries will not be able to travel outside of

constraints.suffix:
their borders, nor communicate with other nations. This was approved by many if not most of the nations of the world, and was backed up by countless experts who agreed that isolation was needed for the world to stabilize itself. With the approval of the world's leaders, the countries of the world entered isolation on the year 2101, remaining isolated from others until the year 2102.

Within the first year, all forms of communication were cut off, and the only way to communicate was through a network of satellites set up across nations in case of a severe emergency, that required the intervention of other countries to aid one another. However, the satellites were never utilized in the hundred of years of isolation. In fact, it appeared as if most countries were fine during isolation, able to recover economically and become stable as experts had predicted. There were no wars or conflicts, and the world continued to move on without major issues that would involve many nations around a singular issue. In fact, the only thing that seemed to really be a problem was that international trade was basically nonexistent. As per the rules of isolation, many countries were prohibited from trading with other countries goods and services. This proved problematic for some countries, but the lack of communication via satellites during the duration of the satellites suggested that those countries would find domestic means to satisfy their resource needs.

The year 2112 eventually arrived, and communications between countries were re-established. However, it was soon discovered that there were major issues that had arisen in the absence of communication and trade throughout the world. Many of the third-world countries had been able to make due during the isolation, but the first-world countries had suffered from the lack of trade, in addition to other economic issues. These countries for whatever reason it may be did not chose to use the satellite communication during the period of isolation, out of pride and fear that the other countries would view them as vulnerable. This was proven to be a fatal mistake, as these countries were not prepared for the monumental challenges that they faced in the return of communication. Many of the countries that suffered from isolation ended up going into conflicts with one another, for resources and other material goods that it had lacked during the isolation. Trade battles and other economic struggles occurred between the biggest nations of the world, dragging the smaller countries into it causing them to suffer as well. It turns out that isolation was not the answer to the world's problems, and that the only way for nations to survive was continue to communicate and work with one another. During the period of isolation, no problems, no wars or conflicts, and no apparent struggles were reported around the world. For those problems were building up and lying in wait, waiting for the end of isolation. In the return to communication, those problems all came rushing out, being much more severe than if the nations never had isolated in the first place.

f6dc009e6d5c4c03a667ca201438077a.prefix:
Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

"Was it all some sort of joke?!" asked
f6dc009e6d5c4c03a667ca201438077a.infix:
the Vice President.

THe President shook his head sadly. "No, it was no joke." He had just gotten off of the phone with

constraints.suffix:
the leader of the United Earth - it seemed that most of the nations of the world had joined the group - and learned the whole story. "It was a desperate defense strategy."

"Defense strategy?" asked the Vice President. "Against what?"

"Us. Or rather the US as it was back then. You're only 45 right? So you've only learned the cleaned up versisn  of our history and that war." 

"Yes, but what does that have to do with anything?"

"Everything. The President back then was ruthless, self absorbed, and determined to put the US in control of the whole world. And our military was strong enough to do it. If it hadn't been for the other nations of the world uniting against us, we would have won. And even then, they were afraid of us recovering faster and trying again. So they came up with a plan to trick us into voluntarily isolating. There is a lot more, but that is the short version."

"So what do we do now?" asked the VP. 

"I don't know," said the President. "I just don't know."

Fortunately the population of the US did know. They were not happy about being tricked into isolation, and they were not happy about the fact that the rest of the world had been working together for 50. But they had become very practical over the period of self isolation and they weren't going to give up, or do anything rash now. They were going to work together to get their country back on its feet and then they were going to start working on the rest of the world.

And so they did. With an emigration from the US to rival the immigration to the US of the old days. US citizens moved to every country that would have them. They brought their work ethic, their culture, and their determination. And slowly the regained the trust of the world. And eventually the US was invited to join the United Earth. 

The US accepted the invitation, and became a full member of the United Earth. And less than 50 years later, the first US territory citizen was elected President of the Earth.

And the rest, as they say, is history.

Growing up, my mother always told me that I was allergic to bees. She would tell me that I should stay away from them at all costs because it would hurt a lot. She did not want to scare me as a child, so she never told me that my allergy could be fatal, but as I got older I learned otherwise. I always avoided spending too much time outdoors, fearing that a bee would get close to me and sting me. I never told anyone about my fear of bees, and I never let it show. Outdoors, my mother always protected me from bees, but when I left for college, she could no longer protect me. She warned me many times to be careful on my own. I always told her that I would be fine, but deep down I was terrified. I stayed in doors as much as I could in my first two years of college, quickly running from building to building in order to avoid any bees. I always wore long sleeves and pants, even in the summer, in order to avoid any stings. My friends never questioned my actions and accepted me for who I was. My junior year of college, I decided to take a summer job in the city. My summer job was being a waitress at a hotel spa/pool. I had to serve customers inside of the hotel, but on occasion, I would need to go outside by the pool. One day, I met a nice boy out by the pool and we got to talking about school. I asked the bee what the first order of business was in the war against the wasps. The bee told me that the first order of business was to find the wasps' queen. The wasp queen had been living in Europe, all the way across the world from my home. I told the bee that I would go to Europe to find the wasp queen. I boarded a flight with my personal bee in tow, and flew to Europe. I found the wasp queen's home in a small town in Germany. I was about to walk in to her home , when suddenly, my mother arrived before me. She told me that she had known about my plan to come to Europe to find the wasp queen, and she had come to stop me. I told my mother I had to do my job as the princess bee and stop the longstanding war. My mother told me that the war had been going on for so long, that it was pointless to stop it. Nevertheless, I pushed my mother aside and knocked on the door. An old woman opened the door and I asked if the wasp queen lived here. The old woman said that she was the wasp queen, and I told her that I was the princess bee. She had been expecting me for many years and invited my mother and I in. We sat at her table and she told me that she had been waiting for me to come and stop the war. She had been the leader of the wasps for far too long and had seen many casualties. The war between bees and wasps was pointless in her opinion and she wanted to make things right. I told her that I agreed with her, and that I wanted to make things right. My mother, the wasp queen and myself agreed to end the war and we signed a peace treaty. The treaty also established a partnership between bees and wasps, so that we could work together and build a better world. I was so happy to have ended the war that I hugged my mother and the wasp queen. My mother and I left Germany and flew back home, knowing that our future looked bright.
